#: app/templates/help/cards-tab-help.htm:6
msgid "Cards Tab"
msgstr "Ripa Kāri"

#: app/templates/help/cards-tab-help.htm:10
#: app/templates/help/function-help.htm:7
#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:10
#: app/templates/help/permissions-tab-help.htm:10
msgid "Overview"
msgstr "Tirohanga Whānui"

#: app/templates/help/cards-tab-help.htm:14
msgid ""
"In this tab you will configure the user-facing aspects of your graph. There "
"are multiple levels to doing so, which are reflected in the levels of the "
"graph tree. <strong>Report Configuration</strong> where you choose the "
"template for the resource report, <strong>Card Configuration</strong> where "
"you'll specify card-related settings, and the <strong>Widget Manager</"
"strong> where you will choose and configure the data entry widget for each "
"node in the graph."
msgstr ""
"I tēnei ripa ka whirihora koe i ngā āhuatanga anga-ki-te-kaiwhakamahi o tō "
"kauwhata. He maha ngā taumata o tēnei mahi, e whakaahuatia ana i ngā taumata "
"o te rākau kauwhata. <strong>Whirihora Pūrongo</strong> e kōwhiri ai koe i "
"te tātauira mō te pūrongo rauemi, <strong>Whirihora Kāri</strong> e tautuhi "
"ai koe i ngā tautuhinga e pā ana ki ngā kāri me te <strong>Pūwhakahaere "
"Taupāngaiti</strong> e kōwhiri ai, e whirihora ai koe i te taupāngaiti tāuru "
"raraunga mō ia tīpona i te kauwhata."

#: app/templates/help/cards-tab-help.htm:19
#: app/templates/views/graph-designer.htm:307
msgid "Report Configuration"
msgstr "Whirihoratanga Pūrongo"

#: app/templates/help/cards-tab-help.htm:23
msgid ""
"Each Resource Model must be configured with a report template. Reports show "
"data for all nodes in a resource instance for which the user has Read "
"permissions."
msgstr ""
"Me whirihora ia Tauira Rauemi ki tētahi tātauira pūrongo. Ka whakaatu ngā "
"pūrongo i ngā raraunga mō ngā tīpona katoa o tētahi tūponotanga rauemi kua "
"whai whakaaetanga Pānui te kaiwhakamahi."

#: app/templates/help/cards-tab-help.htm:24
msgid "No Header Template"
msgstr "Kāore he Tātauira Pane"

#: app/templates/help/cards-tab-help.htm:25
msgid "Lists all node data, no special header at the top of the page."
msgstr ""
"Ko tāna he whakarārangi i ngā raraunga tīpona katoa, kāore he tino pane "
"motuhake kei te pito whakarunga o te whārangi."

#: app/templates/help/cards-tab-help.htm:26
msgid "Image Header Template"
msgstr "Tātauira Pane Atahanga"

#: app/templates/help/cards-tab-help.htm:27
msgid ""
"Use this template for Resource Models that will be be primarily used to "
"record images."
msgstr ""
"Whakamahia tēnei tātauira mō ngā Tātauira Rauemi ka whakamahia hei whakaatu "
"atahanga i te nuinga o te wā."

#: app/templates/help/cards-tab-help.htm:30 app/templates/javascript.htm:535
msgid "Included Image Nodes"
msgstr "Ngā Tīpona Atahanga kei roto"

#: app/templates/help/cards-tab-help.htm:31
msgid ""
"Choose one or more nodes that hold images in this Resource Model. These "
"images will be presented as a slideshow in the report header."
msgstr ""
"Tīpakona tētahi, ētahi rānei o ngā tīpona e pupuru ana i ngā atahanga i "
"tēnei Tātauira Rauemi. Ka whakaaturia ēnei atahanga hei whakaaturanga "
"kiriata i te pane pūrongo."

#: app/templates/help/cards-tab-help.htm:34
msgid "Map Header Template"
msgstr "Tātauira Pane Mapi"

#: app/templates/help/cards-tab-help.htm:35
msgid ""
"Use this template for Resource Models that will be be primarily used to "
"record resources that have a geo-location. There are number of settings you "
"should fill out to control the appearance of the map in the header."
msgstr ""
"Whakamahia tēnei tātauira mō ngā Tātauira Rauemi ka whakamahia hei tāhopu i "
"ngā rauemi whai tauwāhi matawhenua i te nuinga o te wā. Tērā ētahi "
"tautuhitanga me mātua whakakī e koe hei whakahaere i te āhua o te mapi i te "
"pane."

#: app/templates/help/cards-tab-help.htm:38
msgid "Map Controls"
msgstr "Ngā Mana Mapi"

#: app/templates/help/cards-tab-help.htm:39
msgid "Choose whether or not the user has access to the Map Tools."
msgstr ""
"Kōwhiria mehemea ka āhei te kaiwhakamahi kia uru ki ngā Utauta Mapi, kāore "
"rānei."

#: app/templates/help/cards-tab-help.htm:42
msgid "Position"
msgstr "Tūranga"

#: app/templates/help/cards-tab-help.htm:43
msgid ""
"You can set the position by panning the map. On report load, the map will "
"automatically pan and zoom to the resource geo-location if there is one "
"(also see <strong>Default Value</strong> below). Pitch values are 0-60 "
"(higher = more oblique), <strong>Bearing</strong> values can be positive or "
"negative (270 faces west; -180 faces south). Use <code>ctrl + click</code> "
"then pan the map to change Pitch and Bearing."
msgstr ""
"Ka taea e koe te tautuhi i te nohoanga mā te kaurori whakataha i te mapi. "
"Hei te tāutatanga o te pūrongo, ka kaurori whakataha aunoa te mapi me te "
"topa ki te tauwāhi matawhenua o te rauemi, mehemea he tauwāhi (tirohia hoki "
"<strong>Uara Taunoa</strong> i raro iho nei). Ko ngā uara wharara he 0-60 "
"(kei runga ake = he tūpou kē atu), <strong>Ahu</strong> ka āhei ngā uara kia "
"tōrunga, kia tōraro rānei (e anga ana te 270 ki te hauāuru; -180  e anga ana "
"ki te tonga). Whakamahia te <code>Whakahaere + pāwhiri</code> ka kaurori "
"whakataha ai i te mapi hei huri i te Wharara me te Ahu."

#: app/templates/help/cards-tab-help.htm:46
msgid "Zoom"
msgstr "Topa"

#: app/templates/help/cards-tab-help.htm:47
msgid ""
"Zoom levels go from 0 (zoomed out) to 20 (zoomed in). On report load, the "
"map will automatically pan and zoom to the resource geo-location if there is "
"one."
msgstr ""
"Ka haere ngā taumata topa mai i te 0 (topa ki waho rawa) ki te 20 (topa ki "
"roto rawa). Hei te tāutatanga o te pūrongo, ka koripi aunoa te mapi me te "
"topa ki te tauwāhi matawhenua o te rauemi, mehemea he tauwāhi."

#: app/templates/help/cards-tab-help.htm:50
msgid "Geocoder"
msgstr "Pūwaeherematawhenua"

#: app/templates/help/cards-tab-help.htm:51
msgid ""
"Configure which geocoding service the address search bar will use, and "
"whether or not to show the bar at all."
msgstr ""
"Whirihora ko tēhtea te ratonga waeherematawhenua ka whakamahia e te pae rapu "
"tauwāhi, mehemea ka whakaaturia te pae, kārekau rānei."

#: app/templates/help/cards-tab-help.htm:54
msgid "Resource Properties"
msgstr "Ngā Āhuatanga Rauemi"

#: app/templates/help/cards-tab-help.htm:55
msgid "Configure some styling options for how the resource appears on the map."
msgstr ""
"Whirihora i ētahi whiringa kāhua mō te āhua o te putanga o te rauemi i te "
"mapi."

#: app/templates/help/cards-tab-help.htm:58
#: app/templates/help/cards-tab-help.htm:127 app/templates/javascript.htm:236
#: app/templates/javascript.htm:313
msgid "Default Value"
msgstr "Uara Taunoa"

#: app/templates/help/cards-tab-help.htm:59
msgid ""
"Choose whether the map should zoom to the resource geo-location if available "
"or the geo-location of the user."
msgstr ""
"Kōwhiri mehemea me topa te mapi ki te tauwāhi matawhenua mehemea e wātea "
"ana, ki te tauwāhi rānei o te kaiwhakamahi."

#: app/templates/help/cards-tab-help.htm:67
#: app/templates/views/graph/graph-designer/card-configuration.htm:7
msgid "Card Configuration"
msgstr "Whirihora Kāri"

#: app/templates/help/cards-tab-help.htm:71
msgid ""
"The settings for Cards are mostly related yo how you want a user to see the "
"card, but some have a more direct bearing on data structure as well. The "
"preview shows what the card will look like to users."
msgstr ""
"Mō te nuinga e pā ana ngā tautuhinga mō ngā Kāri mō ō hiahia mō te āhua o te "
"mātaki a tētahi kaiwhakamahi ki te kāri, engari tērā anō ētahi ka hangai kē "
"atu hoki ki te anga raraunga. Hei whakaatu te arokite i te āhua o te kāri ki "
"ngā kaiwhakamahi."

#: app/templates/help/cards-tab-help.htm:74
#: app/templates/views/graph/graph-designer/card-configuration.htm:18
msgid "Card Type"
msgstr "Momo Kāri"

#: app/templates/help/cards-tab-help.htm:75
msgid ""
"Choose the Card Component to use. Only the Default Card is available "
"initially, but custom Card Components are a way for developers to enhance "
"the user experience."
msgstr ""
"Tirohia te Wāhanga Kāri hei whakamahi. Ka wātea ko te Kāri Taunoa anake i te "
"tuatahi, engari ka noho ngā Wāhanga Kāri kua āta whakaritea hei ara mō ngā "
"kaiwhakawhanake kia whakapiki i ngā wheako kaiwhakamahi."

#: app/templates/help/cards-tab-help.htm:78
#: app/templates/views/graph/graph-designer/card-configuration.htm:28
msgid "Card Title"
msgstr "Taitara Kāri"

#: app/templates/help/cards-tab-help.htm:79
msgid "Users will see this title when performing data entry."
msgstr ""
"Ka whakamahia tēnei taitara e ngā kaiwhakamahi ina tāuru rararunga rātou."

#: app/templates/help/cards-tab-help.htm:82
#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:32 app/templates/javascript.htm:228
#: app/templates/views/graph/graph-designer/card-configuration.htm:37
#: app/templates/views/graph/graph-designer/graph-settings.htm:44
#: app/templates/views/graph/graph-designer/graph-settings.htm:48
msgid "Subtitle"
msgstr "Taitarararo"

#: app/templates/help/cards-tab-help.htm:83
msgid "Users will see this subtitle when performing data entry."
msgstr "Ka whakamahia tēnei taitarararo e ngā kaiwhakamahi ina tāuru rararunga."

#: app/templates/help/cards-tab-help.htm:86
msgid "CSS Classes"
msgstr "Ngā Momo CSS"

#: app/templates/help/cards-tab-help.htm:87
msgid ""
"You can add your own CSS classes to this Card to customize its look and "
"feel. Define these classes in your project's \"package.css\" file."
msgstr ""
"Ka āhei koe ki te tāpiri i āu ake momo CSS ki tēnei Kāri hei whakarite i "
"tōna āhua me tōna wairua. Tautuhi ēnei momo i te kōnae \"package.css\" o tō "
"kaupapa."

#: app/templates/help/cards-tab-help.htm:90
msgid "Make Card Visible"
msgstr "Meatia Te Kāri kia Kitea"

#: app/templates/help/cards-tab-help.htm:91
msgid ""
"Show this Card by default. Developers could hide a card initially, and show "
"it based other variables."
msgstr ""
"Whakakitea tēnei Kāri kia taunoa. Me huna te kaiwhakawhanake i te kāri i te "
"tuatahi, me te whakakite i a ia i runga anō i ētahi atu tāupe."

#: app/templates/help/cards-tab-help.htm:94
msgid "Allow Multiple Values"
msgstr "Whakaae Uara Maha"

#: app/templates/help/cards-tab-help.htm:95
msgid ""
"While certain node data types allow the storage of multiple values in a "
"single node, \"concept-list\" for example, this setting is how you control "
"cardinality at a higher level. When determining whether or not to use this "
"setting, we recommend testing out the resource editor interface directly."
msgstr ""
"Ahakoa e whakaae ana ētahi momo raraunga tīpona kia maha ngā uara o tētahi "
"tīpona, hei tauira, ngā \"rārangi-kaupapa\", mā tēnei tautuhinga ka āhei koe "
"ki te here i te raupapa tau, i tētahi taumata teitei kē atu. Ina whakarite "
"koe mehemea ka whakamahia tēnei tautuhinga, kāore rānei, e manako ana mātou "
"kia whakamātauria hāngaitia te tāhono takatā rauemi."

#: app/templates/help/cards-tab-help.htm:98
msgid "Enable Card-level Help"
msgstr "Whakahohe Āwhina ā-Taumata-Kāri"

#: app/templates/help/cards-tab-help.htm:99
msgid ""
"To aid data entry users when using this Card, you may want to add some extra "
"guidance. Enable setting to do so, and design the content of this guidance "
"with the Card-Level Help menu."
msgstr ""
"Hei āwhina i ngā kaiwhakamahi tāuru raraunga ina whakamahi i tēnei Kāri, ka "
"taea pea e koe te tāpiri i ētahi atu aratohu. Whakahohea te tautuhitanga kia "
"pērā, hoahoatia hoki ngā kiko o ēnei tohutohu mā te tahua Āwhina ā-Taumata-"
"Kāri."

#: app/templates/help/cards-tab-help.htm:106
msgid "Widget Management"
msgstr "Te Whakahaere Taupāngaiti"

#: app/templates/help/cards-tab-help.htm:110
msgid ""
"Widgets are data entry helpers for each node that collects information; it's "
"often easier to pick a date from a calendar than to type it in, for example. "
"Generally, the data type of the node will determine which Widget template is "
"used. However, in some cases you will have a choice: For example, in the "
"case of a <code>concept</code> node, you can choose a dropdown menu or a set "
"of radio buttons. Similarly, for a <code>string</code> node you can choose a "
"basic text box or a rich text editor."
msgstr ""
"Ko ngā taupāngaiti he pūāwhina tāuru raraunga mō ia tīpona kohi mōhiotanga; "
"hei tauira, he māmā kē atu te kōwhiri rā mai i tētahi maramataka, tēnā i te "
"pato i ōna kupu.   Mō te nuinga, mā te momo raraunga o te tīpona hei "
"whakatau ko tēhea rawa te tātauira Taupāngaiti e whakamahia ana. Kāti, mō "
"ētahi ka whai whiringa koe: Hei tauira, mō te tīpona <code>ariā</code>, ka "
"taea e koe te kōwhiri i tētahi tahua takaiho, ētahi pātene irirangi rānei. "
"Waihoki, mō tētahi tīpona <code>aho</code> ka taea e koe te kōwhiri i tētahi "
"pouaka tuhi taketake, tētahi pūtakatā kuputuhi tāniko rānei."

#: app/templates/help/cards-tab-help.htm:111
msgid ""
"Depending on the Widget, there are more settings you can configure, most of "
"which are optional and all come with acceptable defaults."
msgstr ""
"Kei te āhua tonu o te Taupāngaiti, arā atu ngā tautuhinga ka taea e koe te "
"whirihora, ko te nuinga kei a koe te tikanga, ā, he taunoa papai ō te katoa."

#: app/templates/help/cards-tab-help.htm:112
msgid "Common Settings"
msgstr "Ngā Tautuhinga Noa"

#: app/templates/help/cards-tab-help.htm:115
#: app/templates/views/graph/graph-designer/widget-configuration.htm:18
#: app/templates/views/graph/graph-designer/widget-configuration.htm:21
msgid "Widget Label"
msgstr "Te Tapanga Taupāngaiti"

#: app/templates/help/cards-tab-help.htm:116
msgid ""
"This will be used in the user interface. The default label comes from the "
"node name."
msgstr ""
"Ka whakamahia tēnei i te tāhono kaiwhakamahi. Ka takea mai te tapanga taunoa "
"i te ingoa tīpona."

#: app/templates/help/cards-tab-help.htm:119
#: app/templates/views/graph-designer.htm:312
#: app/templates/views/graph/graph-designer/widget-configuration.htm:27
msgid "Template"
msgstr "Tātauira"

#: app/templates/help/cards-tab-help.htm:120
msgid ""
"The list of available Widgets is determined by the node's data type, though "
"developers can <a href=\"https://arches.readthedocs.io/en/stable/functions-"
"widgets-datatypes/#widgets\" target=\"_blank\">create new Widgets</a>."
msgstr ""
"I takea mai te rārangi o ngā Widget wātea i te momo raraunga o te tīpona, "
"ahakoa ka taea e ngā kaiwhakawhanake te <a href=\"https://"
"arches.readthedocs.io/en/stable/functions-widgets-datatypes/#widgets\" "
"target=\"_blank\">hanga Taupāngaiti hou</a>."

#: app/templates/help/cards-tab-help.htm:123 app/templates/javascript.htm:199
msgid "Placeholder"
msgstr "Puriwāhi"

#: app/templates/help/cards-tab-help.htm:124
msgid "Shown in the input area before the user has entered anything."
msgstr ""
"Ka whakaaturia i te wāhi tāuru i mua i te whakaurunga a te kaiwhakamahi i "
"tētahi aha."

#: app/templates/help/cards-tab-help.htm:128
msgid "If desired, you can define a default value."
msgstr "Ki te hiahiatia, ka taea e koe te tautuhi i tētahi uara taunoa."

#: app/templates/help/cards-tab-help.htm:131
msgid "Other Settings by Widget"
msgstr "Ētahi atu tautuhinga mā te Taupāngaiti"

#: app/templates/help/cards-tab-help.htm:134
msgid "map-widget"
msgstr "map-widget"

#: app/templates/help/cards-tab-help.htm:135
msgid ""
"The map widget allows for a good deal of customization, from the default "
"center and zoom level to default layers."
msgstr ""
"He maha tonu ngā whakaritenga ka taea ki te taupāngaiti mapi, mai i te "
"pūwaenga me te taumata topa taunoa ki ngā paparanga taunoa."

#: app/templates/help/cards-tab-help.htm:138
msgid "datepicker-widget"
msgstr "datepicker-widget"

#: app/templates/help/cards-tab-help.htm:139
msgid ""
"This widget is used for the normal date data type, not the extended date/"
"time format data type. You can set minumum or maximum dates, change how "
"specific the calendar is when user first opens it, or set the display of the "
"date. However, note that real YYYY-MM-DD dates are stored in the database "
"whether no matter what display format you have chosed for this widget. So if "
"you have set YYYY for the <strong>Date Format</strong> and a user enters "
"\"2005\", then \"2005-01-01\" will be saved in the database."
msgstr ""
"Ka whakamahia tēnei taupāngaiti mō te momo raraunga rā māori, kaua mō te "
"momo raraunga rā/wā hōputu tōroa. Ka āhei koe ki te tautuhi i ngā rā mōkito, "
"mōrahi rānei, te huri ka pēhea te tauwhāiti o te maramataka ina "
"whakatuwheratia tuatahitia e te kaiwhakamahi, te tautuhi hoki i te "
"whakaaturanga o te wā.  Ahakoa tērā, kia mārama ka rokirokitia ngā rā YYYY-"
"MM-DD tūturu ki te pātengi raraunga, ahakoa te momo whakaaturanga kua "
"kōwhiria e koe mō tēnei taupāngaiti. Nā reira, mehemea kua tautuhitia e koe "
"te YYYY mō te <strong>Hōputu Rā</strong> me te whakauru a tētahi "
"kaiwhakamahi i \"2005\", ka tiakina kētia ko \"2005-01-01\" ki te pātengi "
"raraunga."

#: app/templates/help/function-help.htm:16
msgid "adding a function - click to view"
msgstr "te tāpiri mahinga - pāwhiritia hei mātaki"

#: app/templates/help/function-help.htm:16
#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:112
#: app/templates/help/permissions-tab-help.htm:47
#: app/templates/help/rdm-help.htm:33 app/templates/help/rdm-help.htm:47
#: app/templates/help/rdm-help.htm:61 app/templates/help/rdm-help.htm:75
#: app/templates/help/rdm-help.htm:89
#: app/templates/help/resource-editor-help.htm:18
#: app/templates/help/resource-editor-help.htm:31
#: app/templates/help/resource-editor-help.htm:53
#: app/templates/help/search-help.htm:8 app/templates/help/search-help.htm:30
#: app/templates/help/search-help.htm:39 app/templates/help/search-help.htm:49
#: app/templates/help/search-help.htm:65 app/templates/help/search-help.htm:88
msgid "open in new tab"
msgstr "huakina i roto i tētahi ripa hōu"

#: app/templates/help/function-help.htm:26
msgid "Define Resource Descriptors"
msgstr "Tautuhi Pūwhakaahua Rauemi"

#: app/templates/help/function-help.htm:31
msgid ""
"This function will generate one or more descriptors for Resources that are "
"created with this Resource Model. These descriptors are used throughout the "
"database interface, but are not saved as part of the resource. This gives "
"you control over the way Resources are identified and described in search "
"results and elsewhere."
msgstr ""
"Mā tēnei mahinga e whakaputa tētahi, neke atu rānei o ngā pūwhakaahua mō ngā "
"Rauemi ka hangaia ki tēnei Tauira Rauemi. Ka whakamahia ēnei pūwhakaahua "
"puta noa i te tāhono pātengi raraunga, engari kāore e tiakina hei wāhi o te "
"rauemi. Mā konei ka taea e koe te whakahaere te āhua o te tautohu me te "
"whakaahua o ngā Rauemi i roto i ngā hua rapu me ērā atu wāhi."

#: app/templates/help/function-help.htm:32
msgid ""
"Once added to the Resource Model, use the appropriate tab to configure a "
"descriptor template. Choose a card, and variables corresponding to each node "
"in that card will be added to the template, demarcated with <code>&lt; &gt;</"
"code>. You can rearrange these variables and add text to customize the "
"descriptor. When you have set the descriptors, click <strong>Re-Index</"
"strong> to update any existing resources in your database."
msgstr ""
"Kia oti tēnei te tāpiri ki te Tauira Rauemi, whakamahia te ripa hāngai hei "
"whirihora i tētahi tātauira pūwhakaahua. Kōwhiria he kāri, e tāpiritia ai "
"ngā tāupe hāngai ki ia tīpona o taua kāri ki te tātauira, ā, ka tohua ki "
"<code>&lt; &gt;</code>. Ka taea e koe ēnei tāupe te whakaraupapa kē, me te "
"tāpiri kuputuhi hei whakarite ake i te pūwhakaahua. Kia oti tō tautuhi i ngā "
"pūwhakaahua, pāwhiritia <strong>Kuputohu anō</strong> hei whakahou i ētahi "
"rauemi o nāianei i roto i tō pātengi raraunga."

#: app/templates/help/function-help.htm:33
msgid ""
"If there are multiple instances of a given card in a Resource, the first one "
"added will be used to create these descriptors. To manually change this, "
"edit the Resource in question and drag the desired tile to the top of the "
"list."
msgstr ""
"Mehemea he maha ngā putanga o tētahi kāri i whakahuatia i roto i tētahi "
"Rauemi, ka whakamahi te mea i tāpiri tuatahitia hei hanga i ēnei "
"pūwhakaahua. Hei huri ā-ringa i tēnei āhua, whakatikaina te Rauemi e "
"kōrerotia ana, ka tō ai i te tāpa e hiahiatia ana ki runga rawa o te rārangi."

#: app/templates/help/function-help.htm:34
msgid ""
"Any user with read access permission to a resource will be seeing these "
"resource descriptors wherever it shows up in search results or on the map. "
"<strong>If a card is intended to be hidden from any group of users, it "
"should not be used in this function.</strong>"
msgstr ""
"Ka taea e tētahi kaiwhakamahi whai whakaaetanga urutomo pānui ki tētahi "
"rauemi te kite i ēnei pūwhakaahua rauemi ina puta mai i roto i ngā hua rapu, "
"i te mapi rānei. <strong>Ki te hiahiatia kia hunaia tētahi kāri i tētahi "
"momo rōpū kaiwhakamahi, te tikanga kia kaua e whakamahia mō tēnei mahinga.</"
"strong>"

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:6
msgid "Graph Tab"
msgstr "Ripa Kauwhata"

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:14
msgid ""
"In this tab you will design the graph&mdash;the core of a Resource Model or "
"Branch. In fact, sometimes Resource Models and Branches are generically "
"referred to as \"graphs\"."
msgstr ""
"I tēnei ripa ka hoahoa koe i te kauwhata&mdash;te iho o tētahi Tauira "
"Rauemi, o tētahi Peka rānei. Me kī, i ētahi wā ko te ingoa ahuwhānui mō ngā "
"Tauira Rauemi me ngā Peka he \"kauwhata\"."

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:15
msgid ""
"For the first step in building a graph, you should fill out the <strong>top-"
"level settings</strong>. Some of these may be changed later while others "
"can't, so make sure to do a lot of testing while developing a graph. With "
"the top-level settings in place, it's time to <strong>construct the graph</"
"strong> by adding nodes (or full Branches) to the graph tree. Along the way, "
"you'll need to set the <strong>node-level settings</strong> for each node "
"you create."
msgstr ""
"Hei mahi tuatahi mō te hanga kauwhata, me whakakī koe i ngā  <strong>"
"tautuhinga o runga rawa</strong>. Ka taea te huri i ētahi o ēnei i muri atu, "
"ko ētahi kāore, nā reira me whakamātautau pūputu i a koe e whakawhanake ana "
"i tētahi kauwhata. Kia oti ngā tautuhinga o runga rawa te whakarite, kua tae "
"ki te wā kia    <strong>hangaia he kauwhata</strong> mā te tāpiri tīpona "
"(Peka Tūturu rānei) ki te rākau kauwhata. I a koe e hīkoi ana, me mātua "
"tautuhi koe i <strong>ngā tautuhinga taumata tīpona</strong> mō ia tīpona ka "
"hangaia e koe."

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:16
msgid ""
"Once you've finished creating this Resource Model or Branch make sure to set "
"its status to \"active\"."
msgstr ""
"Kia oti tō hanga i tēnei Tauira Rauemi, Peka rānei, āta titiro kua "
"tautuhitia tōna tūnga kia \"hohe\"."

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:21
msgid "Top-Level Settings"
msgstr "Ngā Tautuhitanga o Runga Rawa"

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:25
#: app/templates/views/rdm/concept-report.htm:269
#: app/templates/views/rdm/entitytype-report.htm:160
msgid "Identifiers"
msgstr "Ngā tohu"

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:28 app/templates/javascript.htm:339
#: app/templates/views/graph/graph-designer/graph-settings.htm:31
#: app/templates/views/graph/graph-designer/graph-settings.htm:36
msgid "Name"
msgstr "Ingoa"

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:29
msgid ""
"Used to identify this Resource Model throughout the app interface. Default "
"is New Resource Model."
msgstr ""
"Ka whakamahia hei tautuhi i tēnei Rauira Rauemi puta noa i te tāhono "
"taupānga.  Ko te taunoa ko te Tauira Rauemi Hou."

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:33
msgid "Optional subtitle, displayed on the Arches Designer home page."
msgstr ""
"Taitarararo kōwhiri, e whakaaturia ana i te whārangi Kāinga o Kaihoahoa "
"Arches."

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:36
#: app/templates/views/graph/graph-designer/graph-settings.htm:56
msgid "Ontology"
msgstr "Pūnaha ariā"

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:37
msgid ""
"Decide whether an ontology will be enforced in this graph. To learn more "
"about what this means, read <a href=\"https://arches.readthedocs.io/en/"
"stable/ontologies-in-arches\" target=\"_blank\">Ontologies in Arches</a>. By "
"default, you are allowed to choose between using the CIDOC CRM v6.2, or "
"using no ontology. Once a node or branch has been added to this graph the "
"<strong>Ontology</strong> setting <em>cannot be modified</em>."
msgstr ""
"Me kōwhiri mehemea ka whakahautia tētahi pūnaha ariā ki tēnei kauwhata. Hei "
"ako i ētahi atu āhuatanga o tēnei, pānuitia <a href=\"https://"
"arches.readthedocs.io/en/stable/ontologies-in-arches\" target=\"_blank\">Ngā "
"Pūnaha Ariā i roto i Arches</a>. Hei taunoa, ka taea e koe te kōwhiri i "
"waenga i te whakamahi i te CIDOC CRM v6.2 rānei, kia kaua e whakamahi pūnaha "
"ariā rānei. Kia oti tētahi tīpona, peka rānei te tāpiri ki tēnei kauwhata </"
"em> kāore e taea te whakarerekē <em> i te tautuhinga <strong>Pūnaha Ariā</"
"strong>."

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:40
#: app/templates/views/graph/graph-designer/graph-settings.htm:68
msgid "Root Class"
msgstr "Momo Pūtake"

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:41
msgid ""
"This setting is only necessary if an \"Ontology\" has been chosen. Define "
"the ontology class of the root node for this graph."
msgstr ""
"Ka hiahiatia tēnei tautuhinga mehemea kua kōwhiria tētahi \"Pūnaha Ariā\" "
"anake. Tautuhitia te momo pūnaha ariā mō te tīpona pūtake o tēnei kauwhata."

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:44
#: app/templates/views/graph/graph-designer/graph-settings.htm:80
msgid "Configuration"
msgstr "Whirihoratanga"

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:47
msgid "Status"
msgstr "Tūnga"

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:48
msgid ""
"Set to \"inactive\" to disallow use of this graph during development. "
"Inactive Resource Models cannot be used to create new resources, and "
"inactive Branches can not be added to a Resource Model."
msgstr ""
"Tautuhitia ki \"tautauā\" hei whakakāhore i te whakamahinga o tēnei kauwhata "
"i te wā o te whanaketanga. E kore e taea te whakamahi ngā Tauira Rauemi "
"Tautauā hei hanga rauemi hou, ā, e kore e taea te tāpiri ngā Peka tautauā ki "
"tētahi Tauira Rauemi."

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:52
msgid "Resource models that may be related"
msgstr "Ko ngā tauira rauemi ka whai pānga pea"

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:53
msgid ""
"Choose which Resource Models can be related to this one with resource-to-"
"resource relationships."
msgstr ""
"Kōwhiria ko ēhea ngā Tauira Rauemi ka taea te whakarite kia whai pānga ki "
"tēnei mā ngā hononga rauemi-ki-te-rauemi."

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:58
#: app/templates/views/graph/graph-designer/graph-settings.htm:89
msgid "Root Node Data Type"
msgstr "Momo Raraunga Tīpona Pūtake"

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:59
msgid "Choose what data type to use for the root node of this Branch."
msgstr ""
"Kōwhiria ko tēhea momo raraunga hei whakamahi mō te tīpona pūtake o tēnei "
"Peka."

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:63 app/templates/javascript.htm:636
#: app/templates/javascript.htm:644
#: app/templates/views/graph/graph-designer/graph-settings.htm:158
#: app/templates/views/graph/graph-designer/node-form.htm:123
msgid "Description"
msgstr "Te Whakamārama"

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:66
#: app/templates/views/graph/graph-designer/graph-settings.htm:165
msgid "Author"
msgstr "Kaituhi"

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:67
msgid ""
"You can optionally add an <strong>Author</strong> to this graph. Only "
"administrators will see this information."
msgstr ""
"Ka taea hoki e koe te tāpiri <strong>Kaituhi</strong> ki tēnei kauwhata. Ko "
"ngā kaiwhakahaere anake ka kite i tēnei mōhiotanga."

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:70
#: app/templates/views/graph/graph-designer/graph-settings.htm:177
msgid "Abstract"
msgstr "Ariā Matua"

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:71
msgid "You can optionally add an <strong>Abstract</strong> to this graph."
msgstr ""
"Ka taea hoki e koe te tāpiri <strong>Ariā Matua</strong> ki tēnei kauwhata."

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:71
msgid ""
"Users will see this abstract when they are presented with a choice of what "
"Resource Model to use to create a new resource."
msgstr ""
"Ka kitea ēnei ariā matua e ngā kaiwhakamahi ina tāpaetia ki a rātou te "
"kōwhiringa ko tēhea te Tauira Rauemi hei whakamahi hei hanga i tētahi rauemi "
"hou."

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:71
msgid ""
"This abstract will be shown in the Branch Library which is used during graph "
"construction."
msgstr ""
"Ka whakakitea ēnei ariā matua i te Puna Peka e whakamahia nei i te hanganga "
"rauemi."

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:75
#: app/templates/views/graph/graph-designer/graph-settings.htm:189
msgid "JSON-LD Context"
msgstr "Horopaki JSON-LD"

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:76
msgid ""
"Add a <a href=\"https://www.w3.org/TR/json-ld/\">JSON-LD Context</a> for "
"this Resource Model. This allows you to namespace common URI endpoints that "
"are used within a JSON-LD output of the resource. You can enter a plain URL "
"(<code>\"http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/\"</code>), or JSON that defines "
"multiple keys (<code>{\"crm\":\"http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/\",\"rdf"
"\":\"http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#\"}</code>)."
msgstr ""
"Tāpiritia he <a href=\"https://www.w3.org/TR/json-ld/\">Horopaki JSON-LD</a> "
"mō tēnei Tauira Rauemi. Mā tēnei ka taea e koe te whakaingoa wāhi pito "
"mutunga URI e kitea noatia ana i roto i tētahi whakaputanga JSON-LD o te "
"rauemi. Ka taea e koe te tāuru he URL kōkau (<code>\"http://www.cidoc-"
"crm.org/cidoc-crm/\"</code>), he JSON tautuhi i nga kī maha rānei (<code>"
"{\"crm\":\"http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/\",\"rdf\":\"http://www.w3.org/"
"1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#\"}</code>)."

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:80
#: app/templates/views/graph/graph-designer/graph-settings.htm:212
msgid "Appearance"
msgstr "Āhua"

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:84 app/templates/javascript.htm:599
#: app/templates/views/graph/graph-designer/graph-settings.htm:221
msgid "Color"
msgstr "Tae"

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:85
msgid ""
"Choose a color for this Resource Model to be used in the related resources "
"force directed graph."
msgstr ""
"Kōwhiria he tae kia whakamahia mō tēnei Tauira Rauemi i roto i te kauwhata "
"tūtohu whakahau rauemi whai pānga."

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:89
msgid "Icon"
msgstr "Ata"

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:90
msgid ""
"Choose an icon to identify this graph throughout the app interface. You can "
"browse the icons to select one, or type in the search bar to filter them. "
"Arches uses the <a href=\"http://fontawesome.io/\" target=\"_blank\">Font "
"Awesome</a> icon library; custom icons are not supported."
msgstr ""
"Kōwhiria he ata hei tautuhi i tēnei kauwhata puta noa i te tāhono taupānga. "
"Ka taea e koe te tirotiro i ngā ata hei kōwhiri i tētahi, te pato i te pae "
"rapu rānei hei tātari i ngā ata. Ka whakamahia e Arches te puna ata <a "
"href=\"http://fontawesome.io/\" target=\"_blank\">Font Awesome</a>; kāore "
"ngā ata whakarite i te tautokona."

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:98
msgid "Construct the Graph"
msgstr "Hangaia te Kauwhata"

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:102
msgid ""
"Use the graph tree on the left side of the page to construct the graph. "
"Every new graph starts with a <strong>Top Node</strong>, which will take the "
"name of the new Resource Model or Branch. From this node, you can either "
"<strong>Add Child Node</strong> to add a single node, or <strong>Add Branch</"
"strong> to add an entire existing Branch."
msgstr ""
"Whakamahia te rākau kauwhata i te taha whakatemauī o te whārangi hei hanga i "
"te kauwhata.  Ka tīmata ia kauwhata ki tētahi <strong>Tīpona Runga Rawa</"
"strong>, ka whakaingoatia ki te ingoa o te Tauira Rauemi hou, o te Peka hou "
"rānei. Mai i tēnei tīpona ka taea e koe te <strong> Tāpiri Tīpona Tamaiti</"
"strong> hei tāpiri tīpona takitahi, te <strong>Tāpiri Peka</strong> rānei "
"hei tāpiri i tētahi Peka katoa kua puta kē ki te ao."

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:103
msgid ""
"At any point during construction you can switch from <strong>Design</strong> "
"mode to <strong>Preview</strong> to see the full shape of your graph."
msgstr ""
"Ahakoa te wā i roto i te hanganga ka taea e koe te whakawhiti mai i te aratau"
"  <strong>Hoahoa</strong> ki <strong>Arokite</strong> kia kitea te āhuahanga "
"katoa o tō kauwhata."

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:104
msgid ""
"If you have created a branch structure in a Resource Model that you would "
"like to use in a different Resource Model, you can export it from the graph "
"tree."
msgstr ""
"Mehemea kua hangaia e koe tētahi anga peka i tētahi Tauira Rauemi ka hiahia "
"koe ki te whakamahi i tētahi Tauira Rauemi kē atu, ka taea e koe te tuku atu "
"i te rākau kauwhata."

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:110
#: app/templates/help/permissions-tab-help.htm:45
msgid "add a node and branch to new graph - click to view"
msgstr ""
"tāpiri i tētahi tīpona me tētahi peka ki tētahi kauwhata hou - pāwhiritia "
"hei tirotiro"

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:122
msgid "Node-Level Settings"
msgstr "Ngā Tautuhinga Taumata-Tīpona"

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:126
#: app/templates/views/graph/graph-designer/node-form.htm:28
msgid "Node Identifiers"
msgstr "Ngā Pūtautohu Tīpona"

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:129
#: app/templates/views/graph/graph-designer/node-form.htm:40
msgid "Node Name"
msgstr "Ingoa Tīpona"

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:130
msgid ""
"Set the name for this node. This will be used by default in the user "
"interface, but a different name for display can be configured at the widget "
"level."
msgstr ""
"Tautuhitia te ingoa mō tēnei tīpona. Ka whakamahia taunoatia tēnei i te "
"tāhono kaiwhakamahi, engari ka taea te whirihora ingoa rerekē mō te "
"whakaaturanga i te taumata taupāngaiti."

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:133
#: app/templates/views/graph/graph-designer/node-form.htm:85
msgid "Ontology Class"
msgstr "Momo Pūnaha Ariā"

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:134
msgid "only present if this graph uses an ontology"
msgstr ""
"kei konei mehemea ka whakamahi tēnei kauwhata i tētahi pūnaha ariā anake"

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:134
msgid ""
"This setting assigns an ontological class to this node. To learn more, read "
"<a href=\"https://arches.readthedocs.io/en/stable/managing-resources/"
"#ontologies-in-arches\" target=\"_blank\">Ontologies in Arches</a>"
msgstr ""
"Ko tā tēnei tautuhinga he tautapa i tētahi momo pūnaha ariā ki tēnei tīpona. "
"Hei ako i ētahi atu mea, pānuitia <a href=\"https://arches.readthedocs.io/en/"
"stable/managing-resources/#ontologies-in-arches\" target=\"_blank\">Ngā "
"Pūnaha Ariā i roto i Arches</a>."

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:137
msgid "Relationship to..."
msgstr "Te whanaungatanga ki..."

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:138
msgid ""
"Define what relationship this node has with its parent node (the one "
"directly above it in the graph tree). A verbalization of your choice is "
"shown in the <strong>Semantics</strong> section below this setting."
msgstr ""
"Tautuhitia he aha te pānga o tēnei tīpona ki tōna tīpona matua (te mea i "
"runga iti ake i a ia i te rākau kauwhata). Ka whakakitea ētahi whakamārama ā-"
"kupu o tō kōwhiringa i te wāhanga <strong>Ngā Tikanga</strong> i raro i "
"tēnei tautuhinga."

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:141
msgid "Node Data Type and Settings"
msgstr "Te Momo me ngā Tautuhinga Momo Raraunga Tīpona"

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:142
msgid ""
"Depending on which data type you choose, you may have many more settings to "
"fill out. Those listed below will be present for every node no matter the "
"data type."
msgstr ""
"Kei te āhua tonu o te momo raraunga ka kōwhiria e koe, he maha noa atu ngā "
"tautuhinga hei whakakī māu. Ka kitea ērā e rārangi ake nei mō ia tīpona, "
"ahakoa te momo raraunga."

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:145
#: app/templates/views/graph/graph-designer/node-form.htm:144
msgid "Data type"
msgstr "Momo raraunga"

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:146
msgid ""
"Choose the data type for this node. Please see the <strong>Default Data "
"Types</strong> section below. Once data is collected for this node, this "
"setting cannot be changed."
msgstr ""
"Kōwhiria te momo raraunga mō tēnei tīpona. Tēnā tirohia te wāhanga <strong>"
"Ngā Momo Raraunga Taunoa</strong> i raro iho nei. Kia oti ngā raraunga mō "
"tēnei tīpona te kohi, e kore e taea te panoni tēnei tautuhinga."

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:149
#: app/templates/views/graph/graph-designer/node-form.htm:183
msgid "Expose to Advanced Search"
msgstr "Whakatuwhera ki Rapu Ara Atu Anō"

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:150
msgid ""
"If true users will be able to add this node to an Advanced Search query."
msgstr ""
"Mehemea he pono ka taea e ngā kaiwhakamahi te tāpiri tēnei tīpona ki tētahi "
"pātai Rapu Hōhonu."

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:153
#: app/templates/views/graph/graph-designer/node-form.htm:203
#: app/templates/views/graph/graph-designer/widget-configuration.htm:63
msgid "Required"
msgstr "E hiahiatia ana"

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:154
msgid ""
"If true a value must be entered for this node in order to save it. Once data "
"is collected for this node, this setting cannot be changed."
msgstr ""
"Mehemea he pono me whakauru he uara mō tēnei tīpona hei tiaki i a ia. Kia "
"oti ngā raraunga mō tēnei tīpona te kohi, e kore e taea te panoni tēnei "
"tautuhinga."

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:157
msgid "Place node(s) in a separate card"
msgstr "Meatia te(ngā) tīpona ki tētahi kāri motuhake"

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:158
msgid "only present if this node is not already the top node for a card"
msgstr ""
"kei konei mehemea kāore tēnei tīpona i te noho hei kāri o runga rawa mō "
"tētahi kāri anake"

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:158
msgid ""
"If true this node will be set in a different card from its parent. This "
"affects data entry, and you are encouraged to test both states of this "
"setting while building you graph. Once data is collected for this node, this "
"setting cannot be changed."
msgstr ""
"Mehemea he pono ka whakaritea tēnei tīpona ki tētahi kāri rerekē i tōna "
"matua. Ka pā tēnei ki te tāurunga raraunga, ā, ko te inoi ki a koe kia "
"whakamātautauria ngā takotoranga e rua o tēnei tautuhinga i a koe e hanga "
"ana i tō kauwhata. Kia oti ngā raraunga mō tēnei tīpona te kohi, e kore e "
"taea te panoni tēnei tautuhinga."

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:165
msgid "Default Data Types"
msgstr "Ngā Momo Raraunga Taunoa"

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:169
msgid ""
"The data type of a node determines what kind of data that node will store. "
"Once chosen, some data types will require further configuration."
msgstr ""
"Mā te momo raraunga o tētahi tīpona e whakatau he aha ngā momo raraunga ka "
"rokirokitia e taua tīpona. Kia oti ērā te whakatau, ka hiahia whirihora anō "
"ētahi momo raraunga."

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:170
msgid ""
"Developers can <a href=\"https://arches.readthedocs.io/en/stable/functions-"
"widgets-datatypes/#datatypes\" target=\"_blank\">create new datatypes</a>."
msgstr ""
"Ka taea e ngā kaiwhakawhanake te pānui <a href=\"https://"
"arches.readthedocs.io/en/stable/functions-widgets-datatypes/#datatypes\" "
"target=\"_blank\">create new datatypes</a>."

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:173
msgid "boolean"
msgstr "boolean"

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:174
msgid "Use this to store a \"yes\"/\"no\" or \"true\"/\"false\" value."
msgstr ""
"Whakamahia tēnei hei rokiroki i tētahi uara \"āe\"/\"kāo\", \"pono\"/\"hē\" "
"rānei."

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:177
msgid "concept"
msgstr "ariā"

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:178
msgid ""
"Stores one of a series of concepts from the Reference Data Manager. Users "
"will choose a concept in a dropdown list or set of radio buttons. You'll "
"further be prompted to choose a <strong>Concept Collection</strong>&mdash;"
"this controls which concepts the user is able to choose from."
msgstr ""
"Ka rokiroki i tētahi o tētahi rangatū ariā mai i te Pūwhakahaere Raraunga "
"Tohutoro. Ka kōwhiria e ngā kaiwhakamahi tētahi ariā mai i te rārangi "
"takaiho, i tētahi huinga pātene irirangi rānei.  Ka ākina hoki koe kia "
"kōwhiri i tētahi <strong>Kohinga Ariā</strong>&mdash;mā tēnei e whakahaere "
"ko ēhea ngā ariā ka taea te kōwhiri e te kaiwhakamahi."

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:181
msgid "concept-list"
msgstr "rārangi-ariā"

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:182
msgid "Stores multiple concepts in a single node."
msgstr "Ka rokiroki i ngā ariā maha i tētahi aratau kotahi."

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:185
msgid "date"
msgstr "rā"

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:186
msgid "Stores a CE calendar date. See etdf for BCE and fuzzy date handling."
msgstr ""
"Ka rokiroki i tētahi rā maramataka CE. Tirohia etdf mō te whakahaere rā BCE, "
"rā rehurehu rānei."

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:189
msgid "edtf"
msgstr "edtf"

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:190
msgid ""
"Stores an <a href='https://www.loc.gov/standards/datetime/' "
"target='_blank'>Extended Date/Time Format</a> value. Use this data type for "
"BCE dates or dates with uncertainty. This datatype requires extra "
"configuration to inform the database search methods how to interpret EDTF "
"values. Data entry users can enter edtf dates using formats listed in the <a "
"href='https://www.loc.gov/standards/datetime/pre-submission.html' "
"target='_blank'>EDTF draft specification</a>."
msgstr ""
"Ka rokiroki i tētahi uara <a href='https://www.loc.gov/standards/datetime/' "
"target='_blank'>Ngā Hōputu Rā/Wā kua whakaroatia</a>. Whakamahia tēnei momo "
"raraunga mō ngā rā BCE, mō ngā rā rangirua rānei. E hiahia ana tēnei momo "
"raraunga i ētahi atu whirihoratanga hei whakamārama i ngā tikanga rapu "
"pātengi raraunga kia pai ai te whakamāori i ngā uaratanga o te EDTF. Ka taea "
"e ngā kaiwhakamahi tāuru raraunga te whakauru rā edtf mā te whakamahi i ngā "
"hōputu kua oti te whakarārangi i <a href='https://www.loc.gov/standards/"
"datetime/pre-submission.html' target='_blank'>tautuhinga hukihuki EDTF</a>."

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:193
msgid "file-list"
msgstr "rārangi-kōnae"

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:194
msgid "Stores one or mores files. Use this to upload images, documents, etc."
msgstr ""
"Ka rokiroki i tētahi kōnae, neke atu rānei. Whakamahia tēnei hei tuku atu i "
"ngā atahanga, i ngā tuhinga, i ngā aha."

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:197
msgid "iiif-drawing"
msgstr "tuhinga-iiif"

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:198
msgid ""
"Used to store an <a href='http://iiif.io/' target='_blank'>IIIF compliant</"
"a> image."
msgstr ""
"Ka whakamahia tēnei hei rokiroki i tētahi atahanga <a href='http://iiif.io/' "
"target='_blank'>tautuku ki IIIF</a>."

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:201
msgid "geojson-feature-collection"
msgstr "kohinga-āhuahira-geojson"

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:202
msgid ""
"Stores geographic coordinates, and is used to show a resource on the map."
msgstr ""
"Ko tāna he rokiroki taunga matawhenua, ā, ka whakamahia hei whakakite i "
"tētahi rauemi i te mapi."

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:205
msgid "domain-value"
msgstr "domain-value"

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:206
msgid ""
"Similar to \"concept\", choose this to present the user with a dropdown list "
"or set of radio buttons. Unlike \"concept\" this dropdown menu will not come "
"from your system-wide controlled vocubulary, but from a list of values that "
"you must define here."
msgstr ""
"Āhua rite ki \"ariā\", whakamahia tēnei hei tāpae i tētahi rārangi takaiho, "
"huinga pātene irirangi rānei ki te kaiwhakamahi. Kāore e rite ki \"ariā\", e "
"kore tēnei rārangi takaiho e hua ake i tō puna kupu pūnaha katoa i āta "
"whakahaeretia, engari i tētahi rārangi uara me tautuhi e koe ki konei."

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:209
msgid "domain-value-list"
msgstr "rārangi-uara-rohe"

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:210
msgid "Stores multiple domain-values in a single node."
msgstr "Ka rokiroki i ngā uara rohe maha i tētahi tīpona kotahi."

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:213
msgid "csv-chart-json"
msgstr "csv-chart-json"

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:214
msgid "Stores a csv chart formatted as JSON."
msgstr "Ka rokiroki i tētahi tūtohi csv kua whakahōpututia hei JSON."

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:217
msgid "node-value"
msgstr "uara-tīpona"

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:218
msgid ""
"Stores a reference to a different node in this graph. This would allow you "
"to store duplicate data in more than one branch."
msgstr ""
"Ka rokiroki i tētahi tohutoro ki tētahi tīpona kē noa atu i tēnei kauwhata. "
"Mā konei ka āhei koe ki te rokiroki raraunga tārua ki ngā peka neke atu i te "
"kotahi."

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:221
msgid "number"
msgstr "tau"

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:222
msgid "Stores a number."
msgstr "Ka rokiroki i tētahi tau."

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:225
msgid "resource-instance"
msgstr "tūponotanga-rauemi"

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:226
msgid ""
"Embeds a separate resource instance into this node. For example, you could "
"add a node called \"Assessed By\" to a condition assessment branch, and use "
"this data type. This would allow you to associate an individual stored in "
"your database as an Actor resource with a specific condition assessment. "
"Note that this construction is different from making a \"resource-to-"
"resource relationship\". "
msgstr ""
"Ka tāmau i tētahi tūponotanga rauemi motuhake ki tēnei tīpona. Hei tauira, "
"ka taea e koe te tāpiri tīpona e kīa nei \"He mea Aromatawai Nā\" ki tētahi "
"peka aromatawai āhuatanga, me te whakamahi i tēnei momo raraunga. Mā konei "
"ka āhei koe ki te whakapiri i tētahi tangata takitahi e rokirokitia nei i tō "
"pātengi raraunga hei rauemi Kaimahi, me tētahi aromatawai āhuatanga "
"tauwhāiti. Kia mōhio koe he rerekē tēnei hanganga i te hanga i tētahi "
"\"hononga rauemi-ki-te-rauemi\"."

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:229
msgid "resource-instance-list"
msgstr "tūponotanga-rawa-rauemi"

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:230
msgid "Stores a list of resource instances in a single node."
msgstr ""
"Ka rokiroki i tētahi rārangi o ngā tūponotanga rawa ki tētahi tīpona kotahi."

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:233
msgid "semantic"
msgstr "māwhaiwhai"

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:234
msgid ""
"<em>A semantic node does not store data.</em> Semantic nodes are used where "
"necessary to make symbolic connections between other nodes, generally in "
"order to follow ontological rules. The top node of every graph is a semantic "
"node."
msgstr ""
"<em>Kāore tēnei mea te tīpona māwhaiwhai e rokiroki raraunga.</em> Mō te "
"nuinga ka whakamahia ngā tīpona māwhaiwhai ina hiahiatia hei tuitui hononga "
"tūtohu i waenga i ētahi atu tīpona, hei whai i ngā ture pūnaha ariā. Ko te "
"tīpona whakarunga rawa o ia kauwhata, he tīpona māwhaiwhai."

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:237
msgid "string"
msgstr "aho"

#: app/templates/help/graph-tab-help.htm:238
msgid ""
"Stores a string of text. This could be something simple like a name, or more "
"something elaborate like a descriptive paragraph with formatting and "
"hyperlinks."
msgstr ""
"Ko tāna he rokiroki i tētahi aho kuputuhi. I ētahi wā he mea māmā noa tēnei "
"pēnei i te ingoa, he mea matatini kē atu rānei pēnei i tētahi kōwae "
"whakamārama, me ōna hōputu, kuputoro hoki."

#: app/templates/help/map-manager-help.htm:13
msgid ""
"Resource Layers display the resource layers in your database. One Resource "
"Layer is created for each node with a geospatial datatype (for example, "
"<code>geojson-feature-collection</code>). You are able to customize the "
"appearance and visibility of each Resource Layer in the following ways."
msgstr ""
"Ka whakaatu ngā Paparanga Rauemi i ngā paparanga rauemi i tō pātengi "
"raraunga. Ka hangaia tētahi Paparanga Rauemi kotahi mō ia tīpona whai momo "
"raraunga takiwā, horanuku hoki, hei tauira  <code>ngā-kohinga-āhuahira-"
"geojson</code>). Ka āhei koe ki te whakarite ake i te āhua me te kitenga o "
"ia Paparanga Rauemi mā ēnei ara."

#: app/templates/help/map-manager-help.htm:14
#: app/templates/help/map-manager-help.htm:34
#: app/templates/help/map-manager-help.htm:49 app/templates/javascript.htm:588
#: app/templates/views/map-layer-manager.htm:186
msgid "Service Styling"
msgstr "Te Kāhua Ratonga"

#: app/templates/help/map-manager-help.htm:15
msgid ""
"Define the way features will look on the map. The example map has "
"demonstration features that give you a preview of the changes you make. You "
"can choose to use <strong>Advanced Editing</strong> to create a more nuanced "
"style. Note that changes made in Advanced Editing will not be reflected if "
"you switch back to basic editing. For styling reference, checkout the <a "
"href='https://www.mapbox.com/mapbox-gl-js/style-spec/' "
"target='_blank'>MapBox Style Specification</a>."
msgstr ""
"Ka tautuhitia te āhua o ngā āhuahira i te mapi. Kei te mapi tauira ētahi "
"āhuahira whakamārama e arokitea ai e koe ngā panonitanga nāu i mahi. Ka taea "
"e koe te whakamahi <strong>Takatā Hōhonu</strong> hei hanga i tētahi kāhua "
"tōrire kē atu. Kia mārama hoki ko ngā panonitanga ka mahia ki te Takatā "
"Hōhonu e kore e puta ki te hoki kē koe ki te takatā taketake. Mō ngā "
"tohutoro kāhua, tirohia te <a href='https://www.mapbox.com/mapbox-gl-js/"
"style-spec/' target='_blank'>Tautuhinga Kāhua Pouaka Mapi</a>."

#: app/templates/help/map-manager-help.htm:16
#: app/templates/help/map-manager-help.htm:36
#: app/templates/help/map-manager-help.htm:51 app/templates/javascript.htm:395
#: app/templates/views/graph/graph-designer/card-configuration.htm:70
#: app/templates/views/map-layer-manager.htm:183
msgid "Settings"
msgstr "Ngā Tautuhinga"

#: app/templates/help/map-manager-help.htm:17
msgid ""
"You can change the name of this overlay if desired; by default it will use "
"the name of its Resource Model. You make also set the layer to be added to "
"the search map by default, or choose a custom icon for it."
msgstr ""
"Ka taea e koe te panoni i te ingoa o tēnei paparua ki te hiahiatia; ko te "
"taunoa ka whakamahia e ia te ingoa o te Tauira Rauemi. Ka āhei hoki koe ki "
"te tautuhi i te paparanga hei tāpiri ki te mapi rapu hei taunoa, te kōwhiti "
"i tētahi ata whakarite rānei mōna."

#: app/templates/help/map-manager-help.htm:18 app/templates/javascript.htm:590
msgid "Clustering"
msgstr "Rāpoitanga"

#: app/templates/help/map-manager-help.htm:19
msgid ""
"Arches uses 'clustering' to better display resources at low zoom levels "
"(zoomed out). You are able to control the clustering settings for each layer "
"individually."
msgstr ""
"Ka whakamahia e Arches te 'rāpoitanga' kia pai ake ai tana whakaatu rauemi i "
"ngā taumata topa pāpaku (topa ki waho). Ka āhei koe ki te whakahaere "
"takitahi i ngā tautuhitanga rāpoitanga mō ia paparanga."

#: app/templates/help/map-manager-help.htm:21
msgid ""
"<strong>Cluster Distance</strong> - distance (in pixels) within which "
"resources will be clustered"
msgstr ""
"<strong>Tawhiti Rāpoi</strong> - ko te tawhiti tēnei (ā-pīkara) kei roto nei "
"ka tāpoitia ngā rauemi"

#: app/templates/help/map-manager-help.htm:22
msgid ""
"<strong>Cluster Max Zoom</strong> - zoom level after which clustering will "
"<em>stop</em> being used"
msgstr ""
"<strong>Topa Mōrahi Rāpoi</strong> - ko te taumata topa kei tua atu ka <em>"
"mutu</em>  te whakamahi i te rāpoi"

#: app/templates/help/map-manager-help.htm:23
msgid ""
"<strong>Cluster Min Points</strong> - minimum number of points needed to "
"create a cluster"
msgstr ""
"<strong>Ngā Ira Topa Mōkito</strong> - ko ngā ira mōkito e hiahiatia ana hei "
"hanga rāpoi"

#: app/templates/help/map-manager-help.htm:25 app/templates/javascript.htm:207
#: app/templates/javascript.htm:589 app/templates/views/graph-designer.htm:212
#: app/templates/views/graph/graph-designer/permission-settings-form.htm:10
#: app/templates/views/graph/graph-designer/permission-settings-form.htm:57
msgid "Permissions"
msgstr "Ngā Whakaaetanga"

#: app/templates/help/map-manager-help.htm:26
msgid ""
"This tab shows the permissions for the nodegroup whose geometry is displayed "
"in this Resource Layer. Permissions are defined in the Graph Designer."
msgstr ""
"Tā tēnei ripa he whakakite i ngā whakaaetanga mō te rōpū tīpona e "
"whakaaturia nei ōna matawhenua i tēnei Paparanga Rauemi. Kei te tautuhitia "
"ngā whakaaetanga i roto i te Puhoahoa Kauwhata."

#: app/templates/help/map-manager-help.htm:33
msgid ""
"A Basemap will always be present in your map. Arches comes with a few "
"default basemaps, but advanced users are able to add more. Once added, there "
"are few ways to configure each basemap."
msgstr ""
"Ka noho tonu tētahi mapi taketake i roto i tō mapi i ngā wā katoa. Tērā "
"ētahi mapi taketake taunoa ruarua kei roto i Arches, engari ka taea e ngā "
"kaiwhakamahi matatau te tāpiri i ētahi atu. Kia oti ēnei te tāpiri, tērā "
"ētahi ara hei whirihora i ia mapi taketake."

#: app/templates/help/map-manager-help.htm:35
msgid ""
"Define a style for this basemap. Note that depending on the type of layer, "
"there are different styling options. For styling reference, checkout the <a "
"href='https://www.mapbox.com/mapbox-gl-js/style-spec/#layers' "
"target='_blank'>MapBox Style Specification</a>."
msgstr ""
"Tautuhitia he kāhua mō tēnei mapi taketake. Kia mārama, kei te āhua o te "
"momo paparanga, tērā ētahi ara kāhua rerekē. Mō ngā tohutoro kāhua, tirohia "
"te <a href='https://www.mapbox.com/mapbox-gl-js/style-spec/#layers' "
"target='_blank'>Tautuhinga Kāhua Pouaka Mapi</a>."

#: app/templates/help/map-manager-help.htm:38
msgid "<strong>Layer name</strong> - enter a name to identify this basemap"
msgstr ""
"<strong>Ingoa paparanga</strong> - tāurutia he ingoa hei tautohu i tēnei "
"mapi taketake"

#: app/templates/help/map-manager-help.htm:39
msgid ""
"<strong>Default search map</strong> - choose this layer to be the default "
"basemap"
msgstr ""
"<strong>Mapi rapu taunoa</strong> - kōwhiria tēnei paparanga kia noho hei "
"mapi taketake taunoa"

#: app/templates/help/map-manager-help.htm:40
#: app/templates/help/map-manager-help.htm:55
msgid "<strong>Layer icon</strong> - associate an icon with this layer"
msgstr "<strong>Ata Paparanga</strong> - whakapiria he ata ki tēnei paparanga"

#: app/templates/help/map-manager-help.htm:48
msgid ""
"Overlays allow you to incorporate map layers from external sources. Note "
"that Search Results and Search Markets are treated as overlays, and can be "
"customize separately. New overlays can be added with a little behind-the-"
"scenes work. Once added, there are few ways to configure each overlay."
msgstr ""
"Mā ngā paparua ka taea e koe te whakauru paparanga mapi mai i ngā puna o "
"waho. Kia mārama hoki ka whakahaeretia ngā Hua Rapu me te Rapu Mākete hei "
"paparua, ā, ka taea te whakarite motuhake. Ka taea te tāpiri paparua hou, mā "
"ētahi atu mahi iti i muri ka taea. Kia oti ēnei te tāpiri, tērā ētahi ara "
"hei whirihora i ia paparua."

#: app/templates/help/map-manager-help.htm:50
msgid ""
"Define a style for this overlay. Note that depending on the type of layer, "
"there are different styling options. For styling reference, checkout the <a "
"href='https://www.mapbox.com/mapbox-gl-js/style-spec/#layers' "
"target='_blank'>MapBox Style Specification</a>."
msgstr ""
"Tautuhitia he kāhua mō tēnei paparua. Kia mārama, kei te āhua o te momo "
"paparanga, tērā ētahi ara kāhua rerekē. Mō ngā tohutoro kāhua, tirohia te <a "
"href='https://www.mapbox.com/mapbox-gl-js/style-spec/#layers' "
"target='_blank'>Tautuhinga Kāhua Pouaka Mapi</a>."

#: app/templates/help/map-manager-help.htm:53
msgid "<strong>Layer name</strong> - enter a name to identify this overlay"
msgstr ""
"<strong>Ingoa paparanga</strong> - tāurutia he ingoa hei tautohu i tēnei "
"paparua"

#: app/templates/help/map-manager-help.htm:54
msgid ""
"<strong>Default search map</strong> - choose whether this overlay should be "
"shown in the search map by default. Note that in the search map itself you "
"can change the order of the layers."
msgstr ""
"<strong>Mapi rapu taunoa</strong> - kōwhiri mehemea me whakakite tēnei "
"paparua i roto i te mapi rapu hei taunoa. Kia mārama ka taea e koe te huri "
"te raupapa o ngā paparanga i roto i te mapi rapu tonu."

#: app/templates/help/permissions-tab-help.htm:6
msgid "Permissions Tab"
msgstr "Te Ripa Whakaaetanga"

#: app/templates/help/permissions-tab-help.htm:14
msgid ""
"Arches allows you to define user and user group permissions on a per-"
"nodegroup basis. For example, you may want to hide the coordinates of a "
"Resource from the public, or allow a certain group of users to only update "
"the condition assessment section of a Resource Model. Rules like these are "
"all enforced using permissions."
msgstr ""
"Mā Arches ka taea e koe te tautuhi ngā whakaaetanga kaiwhakamahi, rōpū "
"kaiwhakamahi hoki mā te rōpū tīpona. Hei tauira, ka hiahia pea koe ki te "
"huna i ngā taunga o tētahi Rauemi i te iwi whānui, ka hiahia rānei kia tukua "
"tētahi rōpū kaiwhakamahi anake kia whakahou i te wāhanga aromatawai "
"āhuatanga o tētahi Tauira Rauemi. Ka uruhina ngā ture pēnei mā te whakamahi "
"i ngā whakaaetanga."

#: app/templates/help/permissions-tab-help.htm:15
msgid "Permissions Levels"
msgstr "Ngā Taumata Whakaaetanga"

#: app/templates/help/permissions-tab-help.htm:18
#: app/templates/javascript.htm:648 app/templates/javascript.htm:756
#: app/templates/views/components/plugins/workflow.htm:34
#: app/templates/views/graph/function-manager.htm:121
#: app/templates/views/rdm/modals/delete-collection-form.htm:44
#: app/templates/views/rdm/modals/delete-scheme-form.htm:44
msgid "Delete"
msgstr "Muku"

#: app/templates/help/permissions-tab-help.htm:19
msgid ""
"Allows users to delete instances of this nodegroup. Note, this is not the "
"same as being allowed to delete an entire resource, permissions for which "
"are not handled here."
msgstr ""
"Tā tēnei he tuku i ngā kaiwhakamahi kia muku i ngā tūponotanga o tēnei rōpū "
"tīpona.  Kia mārama, kāore tēnei āhua i pēnei me te tuku kia muku i tētahi "
"rauemi katoa, ā, kāore ngā whakaaetanga mō tērā i te whakahaeretia i konei."

#: app/templates/help/permissions-tab-help.htm:22
msgid "No Access"
msgstr "Āheinga Kore"

#: app/templates/help/permissions-tab-help.htm:23
msgid ""
"Disallows users from seeing or editing instances of this nodegroup. Use this "
"permission level to hide sensitive data from non-authenticated users (the "
"public)."
msgstr ""
"Tā tēnei he ārai i ngā kaiwhakamahi kei kite, kei takatā rānei i ngā "
"tūponotanga o tēnei rōpū tīpona. Whakamahia tēnei taumata whakaae hei huna i "
"ngā raraunga whaiaro i ngā kaiwhakamahi kāore i motuhēhētia (te iwi whānui)"

#: app/templates/help/permissions-tab-help.htm:26
msgid "Read"
msgstr "Pānui"

#: app/templates/help/permissions-tab-help.htm:27
msgid ""
"Allows users to see this nodegroup's card. If disallowed, the card/nodegroup "
"will be hidden from the map and resource reports."
msgstr ""
"Tā tēnei he whakaae i ngā kaiwhakamahi kia kite i te kāri o tēnei rōpū "
"tīpona. Ki te whakakāhoretia, ka hunaia te kāri/rōpū tīpona i te mapi me ngā "
"pūrongo rauemi."

#: app/templates/help/permissions-tab-help.htm:30
msgid "Create/Update"
msgstr "Hanga/Whakahou"

#: app/templates/help/permissions-tab-help.htm:31
msgid ""
"Allows users to create or edit instances of this nodegroup. This provides "
"the ability to let users edit some information about a resource, while be "
"restricted from editing other information."
msgstr ""
"Tā tēnei he tuku i ngā kaiwhakamahi kia hanga, kia takatā rānei i ngā "
"tūponotanga o tēnei rōpū tīpona. Tā tēnei he whakaahei i ngā kaiwhakamahi "
"kia takatā i ētahi mōhiotanga mō tētahi rauemi, me te here i a rātou kei "
"takatā i ētahi atu mōhiotanga."

#: app/templates/help/permissions-tab-help.htm:34
msgid "Non-Authenticated Users"
msgstr "Ngā Kaiwhakamahi Kīhai i Motuhēhētia"

#: app/templates/help/permissions-tab-help.htm:35
msgid ""
"You may notice that by default Arches comes with a \"Guest\" group, as well "
"as user named \"anonymous\" who is a member of that group. <strong>Any non-"
"authenticated user is treated as the \"anonymous\" user.</strong> This means "
"that all permissions applied to the Guest group will be given to anyone who "
"views the website without logging in."
msgstr ""
"Kua kitea kētia pea e koe e noho taunoa ana tētahi rōpū \"Manuhiri\" i roto "
"i Arches, tae atu ki tētahi kaiwhakamahi e kīa nei \"Anonymous\", he mema "
"hoki ia nō taua rōpū.  <strong>Me he kaiwhakamahi kīhai i motuhēhētia ka kīa "
"koia te kaiwhakamahi \"anonymous\".</strong> Te tikanga o tēnei ko ngā "
"whakaaetanga katoa kua oti te hoatu ki te rōpū Manuhiri ka hoatu ki ngā "
"tāngata katoa e tiro ana ki te paetukutuku me te kore e takiru mai."

#: app/templates/help/profile-manager-help.htm:7
msgid ""
"The profile manager allows you to update your account information, such as "
"your password, at any time."
msgstr ""
"Ko tā te pūwhakahaere kōtaha he tuku i a koe kia whakahou i ō mōhiotanga "
"pūkete, pēnei i tō kupuhipa, ahakoa te wā."

#: app/templates/help/rdm-help.htm:6
msgid ""
"The Reference Data Management (RDM) enables the creation and maintenance of "
"controlled vocabularies that are used throughout your database. In Arches, "
"controlled vocabularies consist of Concepts, and these Concepts are managed "
"in Thesauri and Collections. In the RDM you can create new Thesauri, create "
"new Concepts, import Concepts from external an endpoint (like the Getty "
"AAT), and -- the ultimate goal -- create Collections, which will be used in "
"your database as data input dropdown lists."
msgstr ""
"Ko tā te Pūwhakahaere Raraunga Tohutoro (Reference Data Management RDM) he "
"tuku i te hanganga me te whakatikanga o ngā punakupu ka āta whakahaeretia, "
"ka whakamahia puta noa i tō pātengi raraunga. I roto i Arches, ka uru ki ngā "
"punakupu ka āta whakahaeretia ngā Ariā, ā, e whakahaeretia ana ēnei Ariā i "
"roto i ngā Papakupu Tairite me ngā Kohinga. I roto i te Pūwhakahaere "
"Raraunga Tohutoro (RDM) ka taea e koe te hanga Papakupu Tairite hou, te "
"hanga Ariā hou, te kawemai Ariā mai i tētahi pito mutunga (pēnei i Getty "
"AAT) ā, - ko te tino whāinga -- te hanga Kohinga, ka whakamahia i roto i tō "
"pātengi raraunga hei rārangi takaiho tāuru raraunga."

#: app/templates/help/rdm-help.htm:8 app/templates/javascript.htm:574
#: app/templates/views/rdm/concept-report.htm:356
msgid "Concepts"
msgstr "Ngā Ariā"

#: app/templates/help/rdm-help.htm:10
msgid ""
"A Concept is a qualitative property that can be attached to a resource, "
"something like \"Stone\" (which may describe a building material) or \"House"
"\" (which may describe a past use for a structure). The advantage of storing "
"these properties as Concepts is that a Concept may have attributes of its "
"own. In the case of \"House\", we could add an alternate label, \"Dwelling\" "
"to that Concept. Then, if a user searches for \"dwelling\", any resource "
"with the \"House\" Concept attached to it will be found."
msgstr ""
"Ko tēnei mea te Ariā he āhuatanga whakamārama ka taea te whakapiki ki tētahi "
"rauemi, pēnei i te \"Kōhatu\" (hei whakaahua pea i tētahi rawa waihanga), "
"pēnei i te \"Whare\" rānei (ka whakamārama pea i tētahi whakamahinga o tau "
"kē mō tētahi mea i hangaia e te ringa tangata). Ko te tino painga o te "
"rokiroki i ēnei āhuatanga hei Ariā, tērā pea ka whai āhuatanga ake te Ariā "
"nōna ake nei anō. Mō tēnei mea te \"Whare\", ka taea pea e tātou te tāpiri i "
"tētahi tapanga tuarua \"Kāinga Noho\" ki taua Ariā. I muri, ki te rapu "
"tētahi kaiwhakamahi i \"kāinga noho\", ka kitea ngā rauemi katoa kua oti te "
"whakapiri i te Ariā \"Whare\" ki reira."

#: app/templates/help/rdm-help.htm:11
msgid ""
"Concepts can also be nested, to allow more complex and meaningful "
"relationships between them. For example, \"House\" may appear next to "
"\"School\" within a parent Concept called \"Building Use\"."
msgstr ""
"Ka taea hoki ngā ariā te whakatauroto, kia puta ai ētahi hononga matatini kē "
"atu, whai tikanga nui hoki, i waenga. Hei tauira, ka puta pea a \"Whare\" i "
"te taha o \"Kura\" i roto i tētahi Ariā Matua e karangatia nei "
"\"Whakamahinga Whare\"."

#: app/templates/help/rdm-help.htm:15 app/templates/rdm.htm:57
msgid "Thesauri"
msgstr "Ngā Papakupu Tairite"

#: app/templates/help/rdm-help.htm:17
msgid ""
"A Thesaurus is an entire set of Concepts which can be imported and exported "
"as a whole. You can create as many new Thesauri as you need, or just add new "
"Concepts to the default \"Arches\" Thesaurus. The organization of your "
"Thesauri has no impact on the way Concepts will be exposed to the public or "
"used throughout the app."
msgstr ""
"Ko tēnei mea te Papakupu Tairite he huinga nui o ētahi Ariā ka taea te "
"kawemai, te kaweatu rānei hei mea kotahi. Ka taea e koe te hanga i te maha o "
"ngā Papakupu Tairite hou e hiahia ana koe, te tāpiri noa iho i ētahi Ariā "
"hou ki te Papakupu Tairite taunoa o \"Arches\". Kāore kau he pānga o te āhua "
"o te raupapa i ō Papakupu Tairite ki te ara e whakaaria ai ngā Ariā ki te "
"iwi whānui, ki tōna whakamahinga rānei i roto i te taupānga."

#: app/templates/help/rdm-help.htm:21 app/templates/rdm.htm:60
#: app/templates/views/rdm/concept-report.htm:344
msgid "Collections"
msgstr "Ngā Kohinga"

#: app/templates/help/rdm-help.htm:23
msgid ""
"Collections, or Concept Collections as they are sometimes called, are custom "
"aggregations of Concepts that will be used in your app as dropdown lists "
"during the data entry process. Collections allow you to reorganize your "
"Concepts for the specific purpose of data entry, so your dropdown lists do "
"not have to look anything like your Thesaurus. You can create as many "
"Collections as you want, or add new Concepts to existing Collections."
msgstr ""
"Ko Ngā Kohinga, tētahi o ōna ingoa ko Ngā Kohinga Ariā, he tōpūtanga Ariā "
"whakarite ka whakamahia i roto i tō taupānga hei rārangi takaiho i roto i te "
"hātepe tāuru raraunga.  Ko tā Ngā Kohinga he tuku i a koe kia whakaraupapa "
"hou i ō Ariā mō ngā mahi whāiti o te tāuru raraunga, nā reira ehara i te mea "
"me rite ō rārangi takaiho ki tō Papakupu Tairite, ahakoa pēhea te rite. Ka "
"taea e koe te hanga i te maha o Ngā Kohinga e hiahia ana koe, te tāpiri Ariā "
"hou rānei ki ngā Kohinga kua puta kē ki te ao."

#: app/templates/help/rdm-help.htm:27
msgid "Example - Create a New Thesaurus"
msgstr "Hei tauira - Hangaia he Papakupu Tairite Hou"

#: app/templates/help/rdm-help.htm:29
msgid ""
"In the video below, a new Thesaurus is created. Once you have made a "
"Thesaurus, you can begin creating a hierarchy of Concepts within it. "
"Remember, the final step will be to make a new Collection and add Concepts "
"to it (from <em>any</em> of your Thesauri)."
msgstr ""
"I te ataata i raro iho nei, ka hangaia he Papakupu Tairite hou. Kia oti "
"tētahi Papakupu Tairite te hanga e koe, ka taea e koe te hanga aroākapanga i "
"roto. Kia mahara, ko te mahi whakamutunga he hanga i tētahi Kohinga hou, me "
"te tāpiri Ariā ki a ia (mai i <em>tētahi</em> o ō Papakupu Tairite)."

#: app/templates/help/rdm-help.htm:31 app/templates/help/rdm-help.htm:45
#: app/templates/help/rdm-help.htm:59 app/templates/help/rdm-help.htm:73
#: app/templates/help/rdm-help.htm:87
msgid "click to view demonstration"
msgstr "pāwhiritia kia kite i tētahi whakakitenga"

#: app/templates/help/rdm-help.htm:41
msgid "Example - Create a Top Concept"
msgstr "He Tauira - Hangaia he Ariā Whakarunga"

#: app/templates/help/rdm-help.htm:43
msgid ""
"The first level of organization within a Thesaurus is a set of Top Concepts. "
"A Top Concept may be something like \"Architectural Styles\" and its "
"children Concepts will be the actual styles themselves. Below, a new, empty "
"Top Concept is added to an empty Thesaurus."
msgstr ""
"Ko te taumata tuatahi i roto i tētahi Papakupu Tairite he huinga Ariā o "
"Runga Rawa. Ko tēnei mea te Ariā Whakarunga he mea pēnei pea i \"Ngā Kāhua "
"Hoahoa\" ā, ko ōna Ariā tamariki ko ngā kāhua ake. I raro nei, kua tāpiritia "
"he Ariā Whakarunga wātea, hou hoki, ki tētahi Papakupu Tairite wātea."

#: app/templates/help/rdm-help.htm:55
msgid "Example - Create New Concepts"
msgstr "He tauira - Hangaia he Ariā Hou"

#: app/templates/help/rdm-help.htm:57
msgid ""
"To create a new Concept, begin by selecting the Top Concept under which it "
"should be placed. This will bring the details about the Top Concept into the "
"main panel. Use the Manage dropdown to \"Add Child\", type in a label, and "
"select the correct language for the label."
msgstr ""
"Hei hanga i tētahi Ariā Hou, me tīmata mā te tīpako i te Ariā Whakarunga me "
"whakauru ia ki raro. Mā tēnei ka whakaurua ngā taipitopito mō te Ariā "
"Whakarunga ki te pae matua. Whakamahia te takaiho Whakahaere hei \"Tāpiri "
"Tamaiti\", patohia he tapanga, ka tīpako ai i te reo tika mō te tapanga."

#: app/templates/help/rdm-help.htm:69
msgid "Example - Add an Alternate Label to a Concept"
msgstr "Tauira - Tāpiritia he Tapanga Tuarua ki tētahi Ariā."

#: app/templates/help/rdm-help.htm:71
msgid ""
"To improve the searchability of your Concepts, you can add as many alternate "
"labels to each one as you want Below, the label \"Dwelling\" is added to the "
"Concept \"House\". The result is that anyone using \"Dwelling\" as a search "
"term will be shown Resources that have the \"House\" Concept."
msgstr ""
"Hei whakapiki i te ngāwari rapu o ō Ariā, ka taea e koe te tāpiri i te hia "
"tapanga maha ki ia ariā e hiahia ana koe. I raro iho nei, kua tāpiritia te "
"tapanga \"Kāinga Noho ki te Ariā \"Whare\".  Ko te hua o tēnei ahakoa ko wai "
"te kaiwhakamahi i te kupu \"Kāinga Noho\" hei kupu rapu, ka kite i ngā "
"Rauemi whai Ariā \"Whare.\""

#: app/templates/help/rdm-help.htm:83
msgid "Example - Create a Collection"
msgstr "He Tauira - Hangaia he Kohinga"

#: app/templates/help/rdm-help.htm:85
msgid ""
"Creating a Collection is very similar to creating a Thesaurus. However, you "
"will be adding existing Concepts to a Collection (potentially from more than "
"one Thesaurus) instead of creating new ones. Below, a new Collection is "
"created. To go further, select the Collection, and use the \"Add dropdown "
"entry\" link to add existing Concepts to this Collection. When configuring "
"the Graph for a Branch or Resource Model, you will now be able to add this "
"Concept Collection to a node."
msgstr ""
"He tino rite te Hanga i tētahi Kohinga ki te hanga i tētahi Papakupu "
"Tairite. Ahakoa rā, kei te tāpiri koe ki ētahi Ariā o nāianei ki tētahi "
"Kohinga (tērā pea mai i neke atu i te kotahi Papakupu Tairite), e kore koe e "
"hanga ariā hou. I raro iho nei kei te hanga koe i tētahi Kohinga hou. Kia "
"hīkoi whakamua ai, tīpakona te Kohinga, ka whakamahi ai i te hononga "
"\"Tāpiri tāurunga takaiho\" hei tāpiri i ngā Ariā o nāianei ki tēnei "
"Kohinga.    ina whirihoa koe i te Kauwhata mō tētahi Peka, mō tētahi Tauira "
"Rauemi rānei, ka taea hoki e koe ināianei te tāpiri i tēnei Kohinga Ariā ki "
"tētahi tīpona."

#: app/templates/help/resource-editor-help.htm:7
msgid "Creating Resource Data"
msgstr "Te Waihanga Raraunga Rauemi"

#: app/templates/help/resource-editor-help.htm:11
msgid ""
"The Resource Editor is used to create new or edit existing Resources. What "
"you see on the left-hand side of the page is this Resource's \"card tree\", "
"which shows all of the data entry cards that you can edit. Think of "
"\"creating data\" as \"adding cards\"."
msgstr ""
"Ka whakamahia te Pūtakatā Rauemi hei hanga rauemi hou, hei takatā rānei i "
"ngā Rauemi o nāianei. Ko te mea ka kitea e koe i te taha whakatemauī o te "
"whārangi ko te \"rākau-kāri\" o tēnei Rauemi, e whakakite nei i ngā kāri "
"tāuru raraunga katoa ka taea e koe te takatā. He mea pai kia pēnei tō "
"whakaaro mō te \"hanga raraunga\" hei mahi \"tāpiri kāri\"."

#: app/templates/help/resource-editor-help.htm:13
msgid ""
"Note that in the demonstration below, the \"Define Resource Descriptors\" "
"function has already been configured to set the Name card value as the "
"resource display name."
msgstr ""
"Kia mōhio koe hei te whakakitenga i raro iho nei, kua oti kē te mahinga "
"\"Tautuhi Pūwhakaahua Rauemi\" te whirihora kia whakaritea te uara kāri "
"Ingoa hei ingoa whakaatu rauemi."

#: app/templates/help/resource-editor-help.htm:16
msgid "basic card data enty - click to view"
msgstr "te tāuru kāri taketake - pāwhiri kia kite"

#: app/templates/help/resource-editor-help.htm:24
msgid ""
"Once you have saved data for a resource, you can see a full summary by "
"selecting the top card. This is the resource report."
msgstr ""
"Kia oti rā anō tō tiaki raraunga mō tētahi rauemi, ka taea e koe te kite "
"tētahi whakarāpopototanga whānui mā te tīpako i te kāri o runga rawa.  "
"Koinei te pūrongo rauemi."

#: app/templates/help/resource-editor-help.htm:25
msgid ""
"In some cases, cards will be nested within other cards, as in the example of "
"adding a geo-location below."
msgstr ""
"Mō ētahi, ka tauroto ngā kāri i roto i ētahi atu kāri, pēnei i te tauira o "
"te tāpiri tauwāhi matawhenua i raro iho nei."

#: app/templates/help/resource-editor-help.htm:29
msgid "nested card data enty - click to view"
msgstr "te tauru kāri taketake - pāwhiritia kia kite"

#: app/templates/help/resource-editor-help.htm:42
msgid "Creating Resources Relations"
msgstr "Te Hanga Hononga Rauemi"

#: app/templates/help/resource-editor-help.htm:47
msgid ""
"In the Resource Editor you can also access the <strong>Related Resources "
"Editor</strong> . To create a relationship between this resource and another "
"in your database, open the editor, find the resource, and click <strong>Add</"
"strong>."
msgstr ""
"I roto i te Pūtakatā Rauemi ka taea hoki e koe te uru ki <strong>Pūtakatā "
"Rauemi Whai Hononga</strong> . Kia hanga hononga i waenga i tēnei rauemi me "
"tētahi atu i tō pātengi raraunga, huakina te pūtakatā, ka pāwhiri ai i "
"<strong>Tāpiri</strong>."

#: app/templates/help/resource-editor-help.htm:48
msgid ""
"Your Resource Model will need to be configured to allow relations with the "
"target Resource Model. If relations are not allowed, resources in the "
"dropdown menu will not be selectable."
msgstr ""
"Me mātua whirihora tō Tauira Rauemi kia āhei ai ngā hononga ki te Tauira "
"Rauemi Ūnga. Mehemea kāore ngā hononga i te whakaaetia, e kore e taea te "
"tīpako ngā rauemi i te tahua takaiho."

#: app/templates/help/resource-editor-help.htm:51
msgid "create resource relation - click to view"
msgstr "hanga hononga rauemi - pāwhiritia kia kite"

#: app/templates/help/resource-editor-landing-help.htm:7
msgid ""
"Choose a Resource Model to begin creating a new Resource in your database."
msgstr ""
"Pāwhiritia he Tauira Rauemi kia tīmata te hanga i tētahi Rauemi hou i roto i "
"tō pātengi raraunga."

#: app/templates/help/search-help.htm:6
msgid "Introduction to Search"
msgstr "He Kupu Ārahi mō Rapu"

#: app/templates/help/search-help.htm:11
msgid ""
"<strong>Search Bar</strong> The quickest way to search the database is to "
"begin typing in the search bar. You'll be presented with database "
"terminology which you can use to create one or more simple filters. The "
"search bar also acts as an aggregator of <em>all</em> currently enabled "
"filters."
msgstr ""
"<strong>Pae Rapu</strong> Ko te ara horo rawa hei rapu i roto i tētahi "
"pātengi raraunga he pato ki te pae rapu. Ka whakaaturia ētahi kupu pātengi "
"raraunga ki a koe ka taea e koe te whakamahi hei hanga i tētahi, neke atu "
"rānei o ngā tātari ngāwari noa. Hei pūwhakatōpū hoki te pae rapu o ngā "
"tātari kua whakahohetia  <em>katoa</em> o nāianei."

#: app/templates/help/search-help.htm:12
msgid ""
"<strong>Search Tools</strong> There are a number tools you can use to "
"explore the database, which are described in detail below."
msgstr ""
"<strong>Ngā Utauta Rapu</strong> He maha tonu ngā taputapu ka taea e koe te "
"whakamahi hei tūhura i te pātengi raraunga, e whakamāramatia ana te "
"hōhonutanga atu i raro iho nei."

#: app/templates/help/search-help.htm:13
msgid ""
"<strong>Search Results</strong> Whenever you change any search filters, the "
"updated search results will be listed here. You can link to a resource's "
"report, zoom to it on the map, or view its related resources."
msgstr ""
"<strong>Ngā Hua Rapu</strong> Ina panoni koe i ngā tātari rapu, ka "
"whakarārangitia ngā hua rapu kua whakahoutia ki konei. Ka āhei koe ki te "
"hono ki te pūrongo o tētahi rauemi, te topa mai rānei ki a ia i te mapi, te "
"tiro rānei ki ōna rauemi whai pānga."

#: app/templates/help/search-help.htm:14
msgid ""
"<strong>Search Panel</strong> The contents of this panel will change "
"depending on what search tool you are using. Typically, the map will be "
"activated by default."
msgstr ""
"<strong>Pae Rapu</strong> Ka panoni ngā kiko o tēnei pae, kei te āhua o te "
"momo utauta rapu e whakamahi nā koe. Mō te nuinga, ka whakahohetia tēnei "
"mahi hei taunoa."

#: app/templates/help/search-help.htm:19 app/templates/index.htm:148
msgid "Search Tools"
msgstr "Ngā Utauta Rapu"

#: app/templates/help/search-help.htm:22 app/templates/javascript.htm:399
msgid "Map"
msgstr "Te Mapi"

#: app/templates/help/search-help.htm:24
msgid ""
"Search results can be represented on the map in two ways: <strong>markers</"
"strong> show the first set of resources in the search results, and "
"<strong>cells</strong> are used to give a general spatial representation of "
"<em>all</em> resources in the search results."
msgstr ""
"E rua ngā ara e whakaahuatia ai ngā hua rapu ki te mapi: <strong>ko ngā "
"pūtohu</strong> ka whakaatu i te rōpū rauemi tuatahi i roto i ngā hua rapu, "
"ā, ka whakamahi ngā <strong>pūtau</strong> i tētahi whakaahuatanga ā-takiwā "
"whānui o ngā rauemi <em>katoa</em> i roto i ngā hua rapu."

#: app/templates/help/search-help.htm:25
msgid ""
"In addition to displaying search results, the map can show resource layers "
"(showing all resources), or custom overlays, if any have been added. You "
"control the visibility of all layers and basemaps with the tool panel on the "
"right."
msgstr ""
"I tua atu i te whakaatu i ngā hua rapu, ka taea e te mapi te whakaatu ngā "
"paparanga rauemi (e whakakite ana i ngā rauemi katoa), i ngā paparua "
"whakarite rānei, mehemea kua tāpiritia ētahi. Ka riro māu e whakahaere te "
"āhua o te kite o ngā paparanga me ngā mapi taketake katoa i roto i te pae "
"utauta i te taha matau."

#: app/templates/help/search-help.htm:26
msgid ""
"Finally, you can add a spatial filter to your query by using the map drawing "
"tools to draw a shape and apply a buffer distance if desired."
msgstr ""
"Hei mea whakamutunga, ka taea e koe te tāpiri i tētahi tātari takiwā ki tō "
"pātai mā te whakamahi i ngā utauta tuhi whakaahua o te mapi hei tuhi "
"āhuahanga, me te hoatu tawhiti parepare, ki te hiahiatia."

#: app/templates/help/search-help.htm:28
msgid "change basemap - click to view"
msgstr "huri mapi taketake - pāwhiritia hei tirotiro"

#: app/templates/help/search-help.htm:37
msgid "toggle search results layer - click to view"
msgstr "takahuri paparanga hua rapu - pāwhiritia hei tirotiro"

#: app/templates/help/search-help.htm:47
msgid "search with spatial query - click to view"
msgstr "rapu me te pātai takiwā - pāwhiritia hei tirotiro"

#: app/templates/help/search-help.htm:58
msgid "Time"
msgstr "Te Wā"

#: app/templates/help/search-help.htm:60
msgid ""
"You can apply a temporal criterion to your query by using the Time Filter. "
"You have the option of creating the filter by hand, or you can use the time "
"wheel. The time wheel is a graphic representation of all the resources in "
"the database, organized chronologically."
msgstr ""
"Ka taea e koe te hoatu paearu wā ki tō pātai mā te whakamahi i te Tātari Wā. "
"Kei a koe te tikanga mō te hanga ā-ringa i te tātari, mō te whakamahi i te "
"wīra wā rānei. Ko te wīra wā tētahi whakaahuatanga pikitia o ngā rauemi "
"katoa i te pātengi raraunga, he mea whakaraupapa ā-wā."

#: app/templates/help/search-help.htm:63
msgid "apply time filter with time wheel - click to view"
msgstr "hoatu tātari wā ki te wīra wā - pāwhiritia hei tirotiro"

#: app/templates/help/search-help.htm:74
#: app/templates/views/graph/card-configuration/card-form-preview.htm:93
#: app/templates/views/graph/card-configuration/card-form-preview.htm:135
msgid "Saved"
msgstr "I Tiakina"

#: app/templates/help/search-help.htm:76
msgid ""
"Saved searches allow you to view pre-made queries. Saved searches are "
"created by database administrators, so the number of saved searches shown "
"here will vary from one database to the next."
msgstr ""
"Ko tā ngā rapu i tiakina ka āhei koe ki te tirotiro ki ngā pātai i hangaia i "
"mua. Ka hangaia ngā rapu i tiakina e ngā kaiwhakahaere pātengi raraunga, nā "
"reira ka rerekē te maha o ngā rapu i tiakina ka kitea i konei, i tēnā "
"pātengi raraunga, i tēnā pātengi raraunga."

#: app/templates/help/search-help.htm:80 app/templates/javascript.htm:594
msgid "Advanced"
msgstr "Hōhonu"

#: app/templates/help/search-help.htm:82
msgid ""
"You can use the advanced search to make more complex queries based on data "
"attributes, or \"facets\". While the basic search filter allows you to "
"combine multiple filters, advanced search is the only way to combine filters "
"with an <strong>or</strong> operator, and also gives you access to more "
"comparison operators."
msgstr ""
"Ka taea e koe te whakamahi rapu hōhonu hei hanga pātai matatini kē atu i "
"runga anō i ngā āhuatanga raraunga, arā, \"ngā whenu\". Ahakoa ka taea e koe "
"te whakahanumi i ngā tātari maha mā te tātari taketake, ko te rapu hōhonu "
"anake te ara hei whakahanumi i ngā tātari whai tohutūmahi <strong>pakari</"
"strong>, ā, mā konei hoki ka wātea ētahi atu tohutūmahi whakatairite ki a "
"koe."

#: app/templates/help/search-help.htm:83
msgid ""
"In the example below, a search is made within a single resource type for any "
"name <strong>like</strong> \"church\" <strong>or</strong> any name "
"<strong>like</strong> \"gate\"."
msgstr ""
"I roto i te tauira i rao iho nei, kua mahia he rapu i roto i tētahi momo "
"rauemi kotahi mō tētahi ingoa ahakoa he aha pēnei i  </strong> \"whare "
"karakia\", tētahi atu ingoa ahakoa he aha <strong>pēnei me</strong> "
"\"kēti\"<strong>rānei</strong> ."

#: app/templates/help/search-help.htm:86
msgid "search for multiple words in names - click to view"
msgstr "rapua ngā kupu maha i roto i ngā ingoa - pāwhiritia hei tirotiro"

#: app/templates/help/search-help.htm:97
msgid "Related"
msgstr "Whai pānga"

#: app/templates/help/search-help.htm:99
msgid ""
"For each resource listed in the search results you can view its related "
"resources with the \"Related Resources\" link under the description. By "
"viewing Related Resources, you get a new view of the database: not how "
"resources are related geographically nor chronologically, but qualitatively."
msgstr ""
"Ka taea e koe te tiro ki ngā rauemi pānga mō ia rauemi e rārangi ake ana i "
"ngā hua rapu mā te hononga \"Ngā Rauemi Whai Pānga\" i te whakaahuatanga.  "
"Mā te tirotiro ki Ngā Rauemi Whai Pānga, ka tiro hou koe ki te pātengi "
"raraunga: kaua ki ngā pānga matawhenua, pānga wā rānei o ngā rauemi, engari "
"mā te kounga."

#: app/templates/help/search-help.htm:100
msgid ""
"There two methods for viewing Related Resources: in a table where each "
"related resource is a row, or in a graph where resources are shown as nodes "
"in a graph, with relationships connecting them."
msgstr ""
"E rua ngā ara hei tiro ki ngā Rauemi Whai Pānga: he ripanga e noho ai ia "
"rauemi i tētahi rārangi, i tētahi kauwhata rānei e kitea ai ngā rauemi hei "
"tīpona i roto i tētahi kauwhata, me ngā hononga tūhono i a rātou."

#: app/templates/help/system-settings-help.htm:13
msgid "Default Application Settings"
msgstr "Ngā Tautuhitanga Taupānga Taunoa"

#: app/templates/help/system-settings-help.htm:20
msgid "Web Analytics"
msgstr "Ngā Tātaritanga Tukutuku"

#: app/templates/help/system-settings-help.htm:26
msgid "Thesaurus Service Providers"
msgstr "Ngā Kaihora Ratonga Papakupu Tairite"

#: app/templates/help/system-settings-help.htm:35
msgid "Map Settings"
msgstr "Ngā Tautuhitanga Mahere"

#: app/templates/help/system-settings-help.htm:37
msgid "Mapbox API"
msgstr "API Mapbox"

#: app/templates/help/system-settings-help.htm:38
msgid ""
"Arches uses the Mapbox mapping library for map display and data creation. "
"Arches also supports Mapbox basemaps and other services."
msgstr ""
"Ka whakamahia e Arches te punakupu mapi Mapbox mō te whakaahua mapi me te "
"hanga raraunga. Ka tautoko hoki a Arches i ngā maheretaketake me ētahi atu "
"ratonga."

#: app/templates/help/system-settings-help.htm:40
msgid ""
"<strong>Mapbox API Key (Optional)</strong> - By default, Arches uses some "
"basemap web services from Mapbox. You will need to <a href='https://www."
"mapbox.com/help/create-api-access-token/' target=\"_blank\">create a free "
"API key</a> (or \"access token\") for these services to be activated. "
"Alternatively, you could remove all of the default basemaps and add your "
"own, non-Mapbox layers."
msgstr ""
"<strong>Kī API MapBox (Kei te tangata te tikanga) (Optional)</strong> - Ka "
"whakamahia e Arches ētahi o ngā ratonga tukutuku mai i Mapbox hei taunoa. Me "
"mātua <a href='https://www.mapbox.com/help/create-api-access-token/' "
"target=\"_blank\">hanga e koe tētahi kī API kore-utu</a> (\"maimai uru\" "
"rānei) kia whakahohetia ai ēnei ratonga. Tētahi, ka taea e koe te tango i "
"ngā mapi taketake taunoa katoa me te tāpiri i āu ake paparanga, ehara nō "
"Mapbox."

#: app/templates/help/system-settings-help.htm:41
msgid "<strong>Mapbox Sprites</strong> - Path to Mapbox sprites (use default)."
msgstr ""
"<strong>Ngā Atakori Mapbox</strong> - Te Ara ki ngā Atakori Mapbox "
"(whakamahia te taunoa)."

#: app/templates/help/system-settings-help.htm:42
msgid "<strong>Mapbox Glyphs</strong> - Path to Mapbox glyphs (use default)."
msgstr ""
"<strong>Ngā Kiriwhi Mapbox</strong> - Te Ara ki ngā Kiriwhi Mapbox "
"(whakamahia te taunoa)."

#: app/templates/help/system-settings-help.htm:44
msgid "Project Extent"
msgstr "Te Whānuitanga Kaupapa"

#: app/templates/help/system-settings-help.htm:45
msgid ""
"Draw a polygon representing your project's extent. These bounds will serve "
"as the default for the search result grid bounds, and map bounds in search, "
"cards, and reports."
msgstr ""
"Tuhia he tapamaha e waitohu ana i te whānuitanga o tō kaupapa. Hei taunoa "
"ēnei whaitua mō ngā tapanga tukutuku hua rapu, hei tapanga mahere i roto i "
"ngā rapu, i ngā kāri me ngā pūrongo."

#: app/templates/help/system-settings-help.htm:46
msgid "Map Zoom"
msgstr "Topa Mapi"

#: app/templates/help/system-settings-help.htm:47
msgid ""
"You can define the zoom behavior of your map. Zoom level 0 shows the whole "
"world (and is the absolute minimum zoom level) and zoom level 20 is the "
"maximum level that most map services support."
msgstr ""
"Ka taea e koe te panoni te whanonga topa o tō mapi. Ko tā te taumata toka 0 "
"he whakaatu i te ao katoa (ā, koia te momo topa mōkito taketake) ā, ko te "
"taumata topa 20 te taumata mōrahi kia tautokona e te nuinga o ngā ratonga "
"mapi."

#: app/templates/help/system-settings-help.htm:49
msgid ""
"<strong>Default Zoom</strong> - Set the zoom level that the map will be "
"shown at by default."
msgstr ""
"<strong>Topa Taunoa</strong> - Tautuhitia te taumata topa ka whakakitea ki "
"te mapi hei taunoa."

#: app/templates/help/system-settings-help.htm:50
msgid ""
"<strong>Min Zoom</strong> - Minimum zoom level defines how far the user can "
"zoom out when viewing the map."
msgstr ""
"<strong>Topa Mōkito</strong> - Ko tā te topa mōkito he tautuhi pēhea rawa te "
"topa whakawaho ka taea e te kaiwhakamahi ina tiro ki te mapi."

#: app/templates/help/system-settings-help.htm:51
msgid ""
"<strong>Max Zoom</strong> - Maximum zoom level defines how far the user can "
"zoom in when viewing the map."
msgstr ""
"<strong>Topa Mōrahi</strong> - Ko tā te topa mōrahi he tautuhi pēhea rawa te "
"topa whakaroto ka taea e te kaiwhakamahi ina tiro ki te mapi."

#: app/templates/help/system-settings-help.htm:53
msgid "Search Results Grid"
msgstr "Tukutuku Hua Rapu"

#: app/templates/help/system-settings-help.htm:54
msgid ""
"Arches aggregates search results and displays them as hexagons. You will "
"need to set default parameters for the hexagon size and precision."
msgstr ""
"Ko tā Arches he whakatōpū i ngā hua rapu me te whakaatu i aua hua hei "
"tapaono. Me mātua whakarite i ngā tawhā taunoa mō te rahi me te tika pū o te "
"tapaono."

#: app/templates/help/system-settings-help.htm:56
msgid ""
"<strong>Hexagon Size (in km)</strong> - Set the actual size of the hex bins "
"that will be shown on the map."
msgstr ""
"<strong>Rahi Tapaono (ā-kiromita)</strong> - Tautuhitia te rahi tūturu o ngā "
"putunga tapaono ka whakakitea ki te mapi."

#: app/templates/help/system-settings-help.htm:57
msgid ""
"<strong>Hexagon Grid Precision</strong> - Set the precision with which the "
"contents of the hex bins will be calculated."
msgstr ""
"<strong>Tika Pū o te Tukutuku Tapaono</strong> - Tautuhitia te tika pū e "
"tātaitia ai ngā kiko o roto i ngā putunga tapaono."

#: app/templates/help/system-settings-help.htm:59
msgid ""
"<strong>Warning:</strong> A large project area combined with a small hexagon "
"size and/or high precision will take a very long time to load, and can crash "
"your browser. We suggest changing these settings in small increments to find "
"the best combination for your project."
msgstr ""
"<strong>Whakatūpato:</strong> Ki te whakahanumitia he rahi kaupapa nui ki "
"tētahi rahi tapaono iti, tika pū hoki/rānei, ka tino roa rawa te uta, ka "
"whakahinga pea rānei i tō pūtirotiro. Ki a mātou me āta panoni mārire ēnei "
"tautuhinga, i tēnā wāhanga, i tēnā wāhanga, kia kitea ai te huinga pai rawa "
"mō tō kaupapa."

#: app/templates/help/system-settings-help.htm:63
msgid "Basic Search Settings"
msgstr "Ngā Tautuhinga Rapu Taketake"

#: app/templates/help/system-settings-help.htm:65
msgid "Set the default search results behavior."
msgstr "Tautuhitia te whanonga hua rapu taunoa."

#: app/templates/help/system-settings-help.htm:76
msgid "Temporal Search Settings"
msgstr "Ngā Tautuhitanga Rapu Wā"

#: app/templates/help/system-settings-help.htm:78
msgid ""
"Arches creates a Time Wheel based on the resources in your database, to "
"allow for quick temporal visualization and queries. A few aspects of this "
"temporal search are defined here."
msgstr ""
"Ko tā Arches he hanga Wīra Wā i takea mai i ngā rauemi i tō pātengi "
"raraunga, kia hua ake ai he pikitia hohoro ā-wā me ngā pātai. E tautuhitia "
"ana ētahi āhuatanga o tēnei rapu ā-wā ki konei."

#: app/templates/help/system-settings-help.htm:80
msgid ""
"<strong>Color Ramp</strong> - <em>not currently implemented</em> The color "
"ramp for the time wheel. For further reference, check out the <a "
"href='https://github.com/d3/d3-3.x-api-reference/blob/master/Ordinal-Scales."
"md' target=\"_blank\">d3 API reference</a>."
msgstr ""
"<em>Kāore te <strong>Rōnake Tae</strong> i te whakatinanatia i tēnei wā</"
"em> - mō te tīra wā. Mō ētahi atu tohutoro, tirohia <a href='https://"
"github.com/d3/d3-3.x-api-reference/blob/master/Ordinal-Scales.md' "
"target=\"_blank\">d3 API reference</a>."

#: app/templates/help/system-settings-help.htm:81
msgid ""
"<strong>Time wheel configuration</strong> - <em>not currently implemented</"
"em>"
msgstr ""
"<strong>Whirihoratanga Wīra Wā</strong> - <em>kāore i te whakatinanatia i "
"tēnei wā</em>"

#: app/templates/help/system-settings-help.htm:86
msgid "Saved Searches"
msgstr "Ngā Rapunga i Tiakina"

#: app/templates/help/system-settings-help.htm:88
msgid ""
"Arches allows you save a search and present it as convenience for your "
"users. Saved Searches appear as search options in the main Search page. "
"Creating a Saved Search is a three-step process."
msgstr ""
"Ko tā Arches he tuku i a koe kia tiaki i tētahi rapunga me te whakaatu anō "
"hei āwhina mō ō kaiwhakamahi. Ka puta ngā Rapunga i Tiakina hei kōwhiringa "
"rapu i te whārangi Rapu matua. E toru ngā wāhanga o te hātepe Hanga Rapunga "
"i Tiakina."

#: app/templates/index.htm:72
#, python-format
msgid "Arches | %(version)s"
msgstr "Arches | %(Ngā momo putanga)s"

#: app/templates/index.htm:80
msgid "Arches Features"
msgstr "Ngā Āhuahira Arches"

